title: apple dumplings
directions: Put all in bowl, except milk and apples.
Cut in shortening like pie dough.
Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Roll out dough on floured surface.
Cut into 8 squares.
Put a handful of apples on each square.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Fold dough up around apples.
Seal.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat and pour over syrup.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off of bones.
Chop.
Cook broccoli, chop up and drain.
Butter 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Put broccoli in dish, cover with the chopped chicken.
Mix sour cream, soup and 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Dot with oleo and sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until bubbles as heated through.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk with spatula. Add lime juice, a little at a time. Add a few drops of green coloring.
Mix well. Put in pie shell or graham cracker shell. Refrigerate a few hours. Frost pie.
Enjoy!

title: turkey with rice stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff turkey.
Bake at 500° until corn pops and blows tail off turkey.
This recipe is for experienced cooks only!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo; add frozen broccoli.
Cover and steam until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into a large greased casserole; sprinkle extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add tomato paste and cook 2 minutes or so, stirring.
Put canned tomatoes in blender for an instant to chop.
Add seasonings and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.

title: glorious mess
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Stir in juice and spices and let simmer 1 hour.
Stir in soup and beans.
Serve hot over chips and top with remaining ingredients of your choice.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Chop 1 1/2 cup of candies.
Reserve remaining for decoration. Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour, soda, and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped candies and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from oven immediately.
Press 3 reserved candies on top of each cookie and allow to cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops, place in oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over pork chops.
Pour tomatoes and juice over rice.
Top with onion and pepper rings.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until rice is done and juice is absorbed.
More juice or water may need to be added while casserole cooks.

title: cherry or blueberry fruit squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add vanilla and eggs (one at a time).
Stir in flour.
Mix well and spread 3/4 batter in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Drop remaining batter by the spoonfuls on filling, spreading it.
Leave some of cherries showing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or when batter starts to brown.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken on bottom, then noodles, soup and broth.
Add crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Add cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, chocolate and evaporated milk in a saucepan.
Cook low to moderate heat, stirring until mixture boils.
Continue cooking over low heat for 5 minutes.
(It should bubble gently.)
Take off stove, add remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into well-buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate (covered with plastic wrap).
Cut into squares.

title: pecan bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup granulated sugar and 1 egg, mixing until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk, 2 eggs and peel, mixing just until moist.
Fold in nuts.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: pooh chicken(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: oatmeal batter bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour scalded milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat in egg and add 1 cup flour to milk mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in yeast, then remaining flour and oats. Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Beat down and put in greased loaf pan.
Let rise, then bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar, flattened with fork, and bake on cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: my mom's tender homemade noodles
directions: Make a well in the flour and drop into it the egg, milk and salt. Mix with a fork and then with your fingers until it forms a very stiff dough. Roll out on floured surface until very thin. Let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and slice into thin noodles. Spread noodles out and let dry at least 2 hours. Drop into boiling soup, bouillon, boiling beef or chicken broth. Cook 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls (marble size) and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy fig preserves
directions: Mix figs, sugar and lemon juice and bring to a boil.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add strawberry jello.
Boil 5 minutes more.
Pour in 3 pint jars while hot.

title: rye bread pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and onion in a pan, then throw in the cheese. Place rye breads on a cookie sheet.
Spread the sausage and cheese on the bread.
Place in a 300° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: va fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sifted dry ingredients, apples and pecans in bowl. Mix well by hand.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Add to apple mixture.
Mix well. Spoon into greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: lamb and string beans
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil until very brown.
Add tomato sauce and 1 cup of water in 6-quart pot.
Clean and slit string beans lengthwise.
Add to meat and celery.
Season.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: apple butter
directions: Add water to cook until soft.
Put all ingredients into pan. Cook about 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Put in pint or quart jars.
Process 5 minutes in water bath.

title: santa fe casserole(serves 6)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add ground beef and onion.
Cook until meat is browned, drain.
Add chilies and mushrooms.
Cook three minutes.
Add salsa and olives.
Cook three minutes.
In a separate pot, bring water to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cook five minutes.
Drain and stir noodles into meat mixture.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onions in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients reserving butter and 1/2 stuffing mix.
Mix reserved butter and 1/2 stuffing mix together, keeping out a small portion for the top.
Put squash into casserole.
Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican pick-up sticks
directions: Combine onions, potato sticks and peanuts.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with butter and stir.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: fantastic fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese and marshmallow cream. Add small amount of maraschino cherry juice or food coloring to tint. Serve with fresh fruit cubes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix in pineapple.
Blend flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add slowly to pineapple mixture until all blended; add walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Place butter, cocoa and white granulated sugar in heavy pot and heat over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup whole milk. Bring to a boil.
Cool and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Ices 2 layers.
Double recipe for 3 to 4 layers.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast pecan halves in the oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely so as not to burn.
Combine pecans, chicken, celery, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Stir together 3/4 of the bacon, sour cream, salt and lemon juice.
Toss with chicken mixture.
Add mayonnaise to moisten.
Pepper to taste.
Sprinkle remaining bacon over the top.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves. Serves 12.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple juice. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place peeled, cut up carrots and onions in bottom of crock-pot.
Place chicken on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn on low, let cook all day.
Wonderful.

title: cherry fruitcake
directions: Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; line with foil, allowing a 2-inch overhang and grease again.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a very large mixing bowl.
Add fruit and nuts and toss until coated.
Beat eggs and rum thoroughly; pour over the mixture.
Toss until combined.
Turn the mixture into the prepared loaf pans, pressing frequently with a metal spatula to pack tightly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, eggs and sliced bananas.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and nuts together (do not overmix).
Add to cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured loaf pan.
Makes 2 loaves.
Let cool.
Can be frozen.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Form into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: crab bites
directions: Blend cheese and butter until creamy. Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture on each half of muffin and cut in quarters. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Yields 96 pieces. Freezes well!

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry romaine.
Break into bite size pieces, discarding veins.
Combine garlic and capers.
Add olive oil; mix well.
Add juices and fish sauce.
Coddle egg by running under very hot water for 2 minutes.
Separate egg; discard white and add yolk to dressing, beating with fork.
Add Tabasco.
Pour dressing over lettuce and smother with Parmesan and croutons.
Ground black pepper at the table.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°; let cool.
Beat the sugar and soft cream cheese.
Add the Cool Whip; blend by hand.
Spread on top of crust.
Dissolve the jello and boiling water.
Add the strawberries.
Put on cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: copper pennies or marinated carrots
directions: Clean,
slice,
then
cook carrots until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Chop green pepper and onion.
In a large bowl, add carrots, green pepper and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Lasts 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar while beating slowly.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, melted margarine and coconut; mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until done.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Stir together beans and taco sauce.
Spread the bean mixture evenly in rectangular dish on bottom and sides.
Sprinkle half of shredded cheese over bean layer.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, oats, onions, allspice, egg, 1/4 cup milk and pepper thoroughly.
Shape to form meat balls.
Cook over medium heat in frying pan sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Turn frequently until browned on all sides.
Dissolve beef bouillon cube in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour over cooked meat; simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove meat from pan.
Mix together the flour and 1 cup of milk.
Add to liquid in pan; mix and cook until thick.
Add meat balls.
Heat if necessary.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper, sliced carrots and diced potatoes.
Put all ingredients in large pot and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until well blended.
Stir in ginger ale.
Chill until jello starts to firm up, but not set.
Fold in pineapple and celery.
Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch dish.
Congeal.
Mix cream cheese and topping until well blended.
Spread on top of congealed jello.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients in this order and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan: crushed pineapple, layer of cherry pie filling, layer of dry cake mix, layer of coconut and layer of pecans.
Melt butter and pour over layers.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well and spread 2/3 on bottom of pan.
Save 1/3 for top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook breasts until tender, remove and cut into pieces.
Lay on bottom of casserole dish.
Empty cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup onto meat and spread.
Top with stove top mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Have your pineapple drained.
Take Eagle Brand milk and add lemon juice.
Add nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker pie crust.
Let stand.
Place in refrigerator.
Makes two 8-inch pies or one 9-inch pie.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, chili sauce, egg, salt and pepper, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Shape beef mixture to form an 8 x 4 1/2-inch loaf.
Place on rack in an open roasting pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until no longer pink and juices run clear. Meanwhile, prepare gravy (recipe follows).
Serve with meat loaf and mashed potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: momma lela's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco to form coarse crumbs.
Add milk.
Mix with fork until well blended. Form dough into ball.
Transfer dough onto floured surface.
Knead gently 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick or thinner (if desired).
Cut with floured cutter and place onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.

title: fajita pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees. Cook chicken in oil, add bell peppers and onions; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the salsa and other seasonings.
Roll pizza crust
and put chicken mixture on top of crust.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: texhoma beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add to beans and other ingredients. Simmer until well blended.
Serve with salad and mexican cornbread.
This can also be put over rice.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and add catsup, sugar, vinegar, salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Stir well and store in refrigerator until ready to serve. This is excellent with the Eastern Style Pork Barbecue.

title: mexican bakers
directions: In a small skillet, heat oil; add pepper and cook, stirring often for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low, add cumin and chili powder and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add beans and salsa, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, baked potatoes.
Top with cheese and onion.

title: almond oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and extracts.
Beat well.
Add oats.
Stir and let stand while sifting flour and soda together. Add to oat mixture; mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Do not overcook; bake about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl or pan.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple conserve
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Cover and store in refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and thawed coconut in large bowl.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake cake according to package directions in round cake pans.
Allow to cool completely, then split layers, making 4.
Place coconut mixture between each layer; cover outside of cake with mixture.
Place cake in covered cake dish or plastic wrap.
Leave in refrigerator for 4 days. After fourth day, you may eat it.

title: quick crisp sugar cookies
directions: Add to creamed mixture.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix and roll into a ball. Roll in pecans and serve with crackers.

title: tempt-me truffles
directions: Gradually add powdered sugar to cream cheese; mixing well after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in almonds, cocoa, coconut or additional powdered sugar.
Chill.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: bedtime drink
directions: In small pan, combine the ingredients and warm over low heat, stirring now and then.
Remove tea bag and serve in your favorite mug.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pork chops, to make a sauce.
Place lean, thin sliced pork chops in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: cally and osco's chicken noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and boil.
Debone chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Add vegetables, noodles and onion to chicken and broth.
Continue to boil until vegetables and noodles are done.
Turn down to simmer and add milk.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 c. juice.

Mix pineapple, pecans, 1 Tbsp. lemon juice, 1 3/4 tsp. Equal Measure or 6 packets Equal sweetener or 1/4 c. Equal Spoonful and cornstarch in bottom of 8" square or 9-inch round cake pan; spread mixture evenly in pan.

title: dressing(for salads)
directions: Mix together.
Pour amount needed over lettuce salad.
Store unused amount in refrigerator.

title: salmon ball or log
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Mix with remaining ingredients except nuts and parsley and chill.
Shape and roll in pecans and parsley.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender; drain well.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in vinegar and beat until smooth.
In a saucepan, bring beet juice to a boil.
Add vinegar and sugar mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add beets and butter.
Simmer a few minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Place 4 cans green beans in a large casserole dish.
Mix in a can of cream of mushroom soup.
Top with dried onion rings.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: yankee doodle dandies(cookies)
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in noodles and nuts until they are evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken or turkey soup
directions: After most of meat has been removed from baking turkey or chicken, put all bones with some meat left on into large pan and cover with water.
Add all ingredients and boil for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool, remove bones, take meat off bones and put back in soups.
Bring to boil again; add 1 to 2 cups small noodles.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup cooking wine just before soup is done.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first 8
ingredients well.
Form into small balls. Bake in oven at 350°.
Brown slightly, then add cream of celery soup plus water to meat balls.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: southwestern cheesy chicken dip
directions: Microwave all ingredients in microwavable bowl on High 6 to 7 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring every 3 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or cut-up vegetables.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger and drain fat.
Mix enchilada sauce and cook 10 minutes.
Add onion, olives and chillies to hamburger.
Put some sauce mix in hamburger.
Put small amount of meat mixture and cheese in tortilla and roll up.

title: smothered steak
directions: Mix soup with half as much water as soup. Add dry onion soup mix. Pour over steak and potatoes. Bake at 350° for 3 hours, covered.

title: lemon fizz
directions: Crush ice cubes and divide between two 10 ounce glasses. Dissolve sweetener in lemon juice, then pour 2 1/2 tablespoons of mixture on top of crushed ice in each glass.
Pour 5 ounces club soda into each glass and stir briskly.
Cut lemon slices halfway through to core and garnish side of each glass.
Yield:
2 cups. Serving size:
1 cup.

title: chili
directions: Saute hamburger and drain. Place in a large pot and add chili mix and water. Mix well. Add beans and tomatoes. Mix and simmer until thick, as desired.

title: pink parfait pie
directions: Empty jello into blender.
Add boiling water.
Let stand 10 seconds to soften.
Cover; blend 10 seconds or until dissolved. Cut package of strawberries in halves.
Set one half aside for topping, allowing it to thaw.
Add other half to gelatin mixture along with ice cream.
Blend until smooth, about 20 seconds. Chill 5 to 10 minutes or until mixture mounds when spooned, stirring occasionally.
Put into pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with strawberries and whipped cream, if desired.

title: candied pecans
directions: Boil all the ingredients until it forms a soft ball in water. Add 2 1/2 cups of pecans and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla. Stir until pecans are coated. Spread on greased cookie sheet and cool. Break apart when cool.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together. Add enough broth to make dough. Roll out on floured board. Cut in strips and drop into boiling broth.
Cook until tender.

title: turnip slaw
directions: Shred turnips, celery and pepper in bowl.
Mix in all other ingredients.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour all ingredients into a hot, buttered (melted) iron skillet and bake for approximately 30 minutes at 400°.

title: frank's favorite date cake
directions: Pour water over dates.
Set aside; let cool.
Combine shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Add cooled date mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Best with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook pork in oil until brown.
Stir in soy sauce, rice, mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Cook until heated.
Make well in center.
Add eggs.
Cover; cook until eggs are half set. Uncover; continue cooking.
Stir to mix.
Serve garnished with onions.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onions and mushroom pieces in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Add mushroom soup to ingredients.
Melt cheese either in microwave or double boiler. Combine all ingredients and serve hot.
Serve with fresh vegetables or corn chips.

title: chili pie
directions: Crush 2 cups of Fritos corn chips coarsely and spread in a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onion and half cup of cheese on corn chips.
Spread chili over onion and cheese.
Top with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sylvia's clam appetizers
directions: Melt butter (margarine) in medium frypan.
(Do not brown.) Saute onion in melted butter (margarine) only until transparent (not browned).
Stir in all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a buttered or Pam sprayed 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned on top. Serve warm.
Spread mixture on additional Ritz crackers.

title: brenda's pasta salad
directions: Mix last 11 ingredients and pour over cooked pasta.
Make day before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid for sauce.
Flake; remove skin. Add 3/4 cup milk, green pepper, eggs, bread crumbs, onion and 1/4 cup melted butter; mix well.
Spoon into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Pack mixture in tightly.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin(6 servings)
directions: Make a medium sauce of butter, flour, milk and cream.
Remove from heat.
Add seasonings, celery, onion and pimento.
Cool. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and crabmeat.
Place in greased individual scallop shells or casseroles.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes, or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: easter eggs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flavoring in about 2 tablespoons of cream.
A little more cream may be used to handle well.
Mix all together and shape into eggs or round balls.
Let stand overnight to set.
Melt chocolate and wax over hot water.
Dip eggs in chocolate and put on wax paper to dry.
Do not have chocolate too hot.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pie pan.
Drain peaches well and reserve juice.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and peach juice in small bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Spoon onto pie within 1/2-inch from edge.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (no more, no less).
Crust turns golden brown, filling appears soft. Refrigerate.

title: pickled beets or eggs
directions: Bring to a boil; add beets or hard-boiled eggs.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Stir in pecans.
Saute about 5 to 6 minutes on low heat, stirring constantly until pecans are lightly browned.
Remove nuts from pan with slotted spoon.
Allow to drain on paper towels.
Dust in the 1/4 cup sugar.
While these air-dry for 5 minutes, combine remaining ingredients in ice cream maker container.
Stir in sugared pecans.
Pack in 3 parts ice and 1 part ice cream salt.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lisa's chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into well greased bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: For best results, use fresh ingredients.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Beat egg with 1/2 cup water and vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
You may refrigerate for several days.

title: aunt leslie's cantonese sauce for lamb
directions: Marinate lamb for 24 hours after combining marinade ingredients.
Bake at 225°, using meat thermometer, basting every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad(favorite recipe)
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice.
Drain orange slices, reserving juice.
Drain cherries.
Place all fruit (except bananas) in serving bowl.
Combine 2 cups pineapple juice (use juice from orange slices if there is not enough pineapple juice) with vanilla pudding.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and transparent.
Pour over fruit in serving bowl.
Chill.
Add bananas right before serving.

title: turkey or chicken log
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients.
Blend in next 2 ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Shape into log; refrigerate overnight.
Toss together the remaining parsley and nuts.
Use to coat log.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: babootie(hamburg dish - far east style)
directions: Fry beef and onions.
Add other ingredients.
Serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: banana bread(india house-nantucket)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan, then set on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.
If desired, 3/4 cup chopped walnuts may be added.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil in saucepan.
Add chopped vegetables and spices to drained sauerkraut.
Pour syrup over the vegetables.
Store in refrigerator in covered jars.
This improves with age; keeps extremely well.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening in heavy pan.
Add all other ingredients and cover tightly.
Cook on slow fire, stirring occasionally until chops are tender.
Remove cover and let brown. Add more water if needed.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Pour half of this over well beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remainder of syrup for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour the rest over egg whites.
Beat until cool.
Add nuts and beat until you spoon it out on wax paper. Makes about 24.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice 5 minutes less than package directions.
Mix with remaining ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese; mix with softened margarine.
Mix flour, pepper and salt.
Gradually mix flour into cheese.
Last, mix Rice Krispies and make 1 large ball.
Pinch off quarter size pieces and flatten slightly on baking pan.
You may need to add a little flour to keep dough from getting sticky.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake for 8 minutes or until just starting to turn brown.

title: chili-baked chicken drumsticks
directions: In large bowl mix chili powder, cumin, hot paprika, oregano, salt and ground pepper in boiling water and cool.
Mix in beaten egg, ketchup and hot pepper sauce.
Add drumsticks.
Toss and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Remove from marinade and roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together margarine and brown sugar and add flour, eggs, pecans and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch pan. Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk. Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture. Beat in molasses.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake one hour or until sharp knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve slightly warm or room temperature.
Makes 9 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
In a separate bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel and Ranch Style beans.
Add to meat mixture and heat.
Place a layer of Doritos chips in a baking dish.
Pour mixture over chips.
Add grated cheese to top.
Bake in conventional oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, apples and oranges through food grinder, using coarse blade.
Add sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Add nutmeats and grapes; chill.
May serve as it or molded.
Dissolve 2 packages of gelatin in 1 cup boiling water and chill until syrupy. Add to cranberry mixture and chill until set.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil in saucepan.
Slice pickles in half lengthwise.
Reserve some pickle juice.
Place 2 or 3 garlic cloves in bottom of empty pickle jar; add sliced pickles. Pour hot vinegar mixture over pickles; add the reserved pickle juice if vinegar mix does not cover pickles totally.
Refrigerate for 3 days before using.
Excellent to have on hand in refrigerator.

title: italian rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to recipe on the box.
While rice is cooking, brown and drain sausage.
Drain tomatoes.
In a bowl, mix together cooked rice, sausage, olives, green peppers, tomatoes and half of the Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Transfer to a baking dish and sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cut away tubes and outer membrane from liver.
Wash liver in cold water; dry.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Heat cooking oil in skillet; saute onions until transparent.
Set onions aside and brown liver on both sides (5 minutes).
Place onions in pan with water.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onion to desired thickness.
Mix seasoned salt, salt, pepper and flour together.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt into buttermilk.
Put onion rings in flour, then in buttermilk and back into the flour mixture.
Do this twice.
Deep fry in deep fryer at 300°.
Let fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in 9-inch unbaked pie crust for about 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: orange bread
directions: Boil the peelings in a potful of water 1 hour.
Peel the white off the peeling with a spoon and discard the white.
Cut the orange peels in small pieces and cook them with 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Boil them until the water almost disappears.
Make a batter of the remaining ingredients.
Mix the prepared orange peels into the batter.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat the soups, chilies, broth and milk. Set aside. Layer 9 x 13 casserole as follows: tortillas, mixture, onion, cheese (save enough for top layer) and chicken. Bake at 400° (until it bubbles) for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine 1 cup brown sugar, water, butter and corn syrup.
Cook until a small amount forms a soft ball in cold water.
Scald milk. Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, cornstarch and flour.
Mix well. Add scalded milk and cook for 15 minutes or until thick and smooth.
Pour in beaten egg yolks and cook for 1 minute longer. Add butterscotch mixture.
Pour into baked shell and cover with meringue and brown.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add Ragu sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Pour over macaroni.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan until bubbly.

title: sauteed vegetables
directions: Saute all vegetables in salad oil; sprinkle with soy sauce and teriyaki.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Saute 5 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with rice.
Cover rice with about 2 1/2 cups water.
Sprinkle 1/2 package dry onion soup over water and rice.
Lay chicken pieces over rice and water (legs, thighs, breasts; remove skin).
Cover with 2/3 can of golden mushroom soup; spread evenly.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first three ingredients until syrup spins a thread.
Add butter, vanilla and peanuts.
Cook until peanuts are done and brown.
Remove from fire and add soda.
Stir quickly and pour into buttered pie pans.
Beat pie pans until candy spreads evenly over bottom.
Makes 7 or 8 patties.

title: tropical relish
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Quarter lemon, remove seeds and put through chopper.
Add pineapple and blend all with sugar.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours before serving.
Makes 1 quart relish.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add boiling water and then oil and then food coloring.
Store in covered container or Ziploc bags to keep moist.
You may use dry, unsweetened jello mix or Kool-Aid mixes to make colors that may not be available by using food coloring.

title: barbacoa(roasted beef)
directions: Turn on crock-pot and place meat in.
Make slices in meat and put cloves of garlic in.
Sprinkle meat with cumin and chili powder.
Place bay leaves on top.
Add water and sprinkle with salt.
Cook on high for 8 hours or low all day.
When meat is done and very tender, remove from pot and cool.
Shred beef with fingers and place back in crock-pot, along with the juices that are already in there.
Salt to taste.
Serve with flour or corn tortillas, salsa (pico de gaio), shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Grind cranberries and apples. Add pineapple and sugar; let set overnight.
Next day, add nuts. Dissolve jello in 1 cup water and pineapple juice.
Add to mixture and pour into mold or bowl.

title: fancy dessert
directions: Make a crust by crumbling together crust ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: christmas holly
directions: Mix all ingredients until coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Put red hots onto look alike holly.

title: elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Brown meat in oil.
Add onions. Blend in soup, mushroom liquid, mushrooms and garlic.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, in covered casserole dish.
Serve on rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together with electric mixer.
Serve with chips.

title: ma-ma's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add water and
milk.
Stir constantly and cook until thick.
Add butter and serve with hot biscuits.

title: hot cranberry apple cider
directions: Mix juices and sugar in pot. Break cinnamon sticks and put with cloves in spice ball. Cook on low boil for 10 minutes. Remove spice ball. Keep hot to serve.

title: lo-cal pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and chill.
Mix with and blend in cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Mix and blend cream cheese, yogurt and salad dressing; pour over veggies.

title: golden broiled chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, salt and seasonings with egg and onion in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add chicken to mixture and let stand at room temperature, covered, for 1 hour.
Place chicken skin side down, 7 to 9 inches from heat.
Broil 30 minutes basting frequently.
Turn chicken and baste.
Broil 15 minutes more.
Chicken should be tender and golden.

title: "brown" rice
directions: Melt margarine in the chosen casserole dish.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/3 cup of soup with hamburger, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 to 8 oval patties. Brown patties in skillet; drain.
Gradually blend remaining soup into flour until smooth.
Add to skillet remaining ingredients. Stir and cover.
Cover over low heat 20 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.

title: apricot glazed chicken with stuffing
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Add water to make 1 cup. Set aside.
Brown chicken in hot oil in skillet.
Add water/syrup mixture, margarine, sugar, vinegar and allspice.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in stuffing mix and apricots.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Bring milk and 2 tablespoons butter to slight boil.
Mix with batter.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Mix last 5 ingredients together and spread on cake while cake is still warm.
Broil until topping is bubbly and brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve 1 package German's sweet chocolate, grated, in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream Crisco or butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to remaining buttermilk and add to the mixture.
Add chocolate and water (cooled).
Then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 well-greased lightly floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cake cool slightly in pan.
Layers are very tender when warm.

title: oven baked cranberry barbecued chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in cooking oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a large baking dish.
In same skillet, cook onion and celery until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through and skim off excess fat.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, basting 2 to 3 times during baking.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Remove all seeds and let sit on paper towels to drain most of juice.
Place paper towels over tomatoes and press lightly to remove excess.
Measure 5 to 6 cups. Cut lemons into very thin slices, then quarter slices.
Combine all ingredients in a pot.
Place over medium to hot heat; bring to boil.
Stir frequently so it won't stick.
When it thickens, put in sterilized jars and add one cinnamon stick to each jar.
Seal. Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes to complete seal.
Makes 4 pint jars or eight 8 ounce jars.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Mix together the taco seasoning mix and sour cream.
Layer beans, sour cream mix, tomatoes, onions, cheese and olives in 8 x 12-inch dish.

title: baked empanitas(apple turnovers)
directions: Add flour, salt and shortening.
Cream butter with cream cheese until fluffy and mix with flour mixture until a smooth ball is formed.
Wrap well with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
When removed from refrigerator, roll out dough on floured surface.
Cut 3-inch triangles (or round).
Place 1 tablespoon of applesauce on each round, fold over and seal edges.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peppermint surprise
directions: Crush candy; add light cream.
Heat in double boiler until "mushy".
Add gelatin, dissolved in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Break cookies in half and line sides of pan.
Line bottom of pan with cookies.
Pour in half of peppermint mixture, another layer of cookies and rest of peppermint mixture.
Top with cookies.
Chill 12 to 24 hours.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chips side by side on cookie sheet and warm in oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on each chip.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted (4 to 5 minutes).

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat and add eggs, one at a	time.
Add graham cracker crumbs and baking powder, which has been
mixed
with
milk.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken stroganoff
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook half of the chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms and onion until vegetables are tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Garnish with red and green pepper, if desired.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and parsley; shape into 24 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs.
Pour off drippings. Stir in soup, water and pickle.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gram's doughnuts(from grange cookbook, dated 1940)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Combine sugar and eggs.
Add shortening and beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add milk and dry ingredients; mix thoroughly until smooth.
Handle as little as possible and roll dough on floured board 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until golden brown, turning frequently. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen small doughnuts.

title: basic whole wheat mix
directions: Sift flour.
Stir in baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift together 2 times into a large bowl.
Add milk and mix thoroughly. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mix feels like cornmeal.
Store in tightly covered container at room temperature.

title: cherry buns
directions: Measure 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sugar in small bowl.
Stir. Roll biscuits in this mixture.
Place in round dish.
Press a hollow in each biscuit.
Put 1 heaping teaspoon of pie filling in each hollow.
Sprinkle leftover mix on top.
Bake on Medium power in microwave for 6 minutes.
(You will need to turn them if your microwave has no turntable.
Turn at 3 minutes.)
They are done if the top springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Place confectioners sugar, vanilla and milk in a small bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Drizzle over buns.
Sprinkle a little extra cinnamon on top.

title: quick and easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, then raspberry jello powder.
Sprinkle cake mix over jello. Pour water over cake mix, then drizzle melted margarine over top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot sauce or taco sauce
directions: Taste to adjust seasoning. Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer for about 1 hour, stirring often. Yield: approximately 1 1/2 gallons.

title: serbian fish
directions: Thaw fish.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch pieces; salt and pepper and dip in flour.
Brown on each side in oil.
Remove pieces to a platter. Combine onions, green pepper, tomatoes, garlic, celery, water and brown sugar.
Cover over low heat about 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup of oil and catsup.
Stir well.
In a large 12 x 15-inch pan, pour 1/2 of the cooked sauce.
Place fish on sauce and pour remaining sauce over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until tender.
Remove from heat; add all other ingredients (except cheese and chips).
Mix well, then cover with chips (crumbled) and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Break up crackers with hands or food processor and add to egg white mixture.
Add nuts; mix and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix raisins, orange juice and water.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Mix together sugar and flour.
Stirring constantly, slowly pour sugar mixture into raisin mixture.
Cook until thick (a few minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and nuts (if desired).
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and add a pastry top. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Place in pie crust.
In heavy saucepan, add jello, sugar and cornstarch.
Mix together well. Add water and stir with wooden spoon.
Turn burner on high.
Stir mixture often.
After it starts boiling, reduce heat to medium and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over peaches. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry cream cheese muffins
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and 2 tablespoons sugar until smooth; set aside.
Place the bread mix in another bowl.
Combine the milk, oil and egg; stir into bread mix just until moistened.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups one-fourth full with batter.
Place 2 teaspoons cream cheese mixture in the center of each; top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: flowerpot cake(alice's kitchen)
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding by itself with milk; set aside.
Mix everything together except Oreos. Process Oreos.
Layer mixture and Oreos, ending with Oreos.

title: gringo bean casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven or heavy casserole, saute bell peppers, onions and celery in butter until soft.
Then add the tomatoes and beans; cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring now and then to avoid sticking.
Finally, stir in the grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients, mixing together.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and crackers.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: velvet almond fudge pie
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside. Blend
together
until
smooth,
pie filling mix, corn syrup, milk,
egg	and
chips.
Add
almonds and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or until top is firm and begins to crack.
Cool at least 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: hot spiced fruit tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove bags.
Combine tea, sugar, juices and spices in a large Dutch oven.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: white castle hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix beef and soup mix.
Press mixture into large cookie sheet (must be thin).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Drain grease.
Cut meat into 40 squares.
Place 1 meat square, 1 cheese and 1 pickle slice on each roll.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil and put in a 325° oven until hot, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, pecans (1 cup), green pepper, onion and salt. Shape into two balls and roll in remaining nuts. Wrap in plastic wrap and foil. Refrigerate overnight. Serve with assorted crackers. Makes two balls.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Break half of the cake into small pieces.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat egg yolks until light. Add butter, sugar and vanilla. Beat well.
Mix with cream that is already whipped.
Pour half over cake layer, then crumble half of the candy bars over cream mixture.
Repeat with rest of cake, cream mixture and candy bars. Cover with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: quick potato bake
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place in a large, plastic bag with oil and soup mix and shake to coat potatoes.
Pour in baking dish and discard plastic bag.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg-ham dish
directions: Place 4 slices of bread on bottom of baking dish.
Put remaining ingredients on top.
Place other 4 slices of bread on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Toast English muffin halves in broiler or toaster.
Spread two tablespoons of spaghetti or pizza sauce on muffin.
Top with meat of your choice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses. Place in broiler until cheese melts, approximately 5 minutes.

title: hot or cold spiced tea
directions: Place 1 or 2 teaspoons of mixture in cup and add boiling or ice water.

title: cheddar pennies
directions: Blend margarine and cheese spread.
Add flour; mix and chill. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Lay on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in freezer containers.
Remove from freezer.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes about 40 pennies.
Should be soft when done.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream.
Add almond flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put a layer of batter in bottom of pan.
Add half of cranberry sauce.
Put remaining batter on top.
Add remaining cranberry sauce and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Blend cornmeal mix and baking powder and add to liquid mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: *BLKLIN incense from Sheba, and the sweet cane from a far country."

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in margarine; drain off margarine and reserve for toasted crumbs.
Mix soups and salad dressing and add to first ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Mix seafoods together and add to mixture in a large greased casserole or pan.
Put a layer of rice and a layer of seafood mixture until all is used.
Top with toasted buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions and drain well. In medium bowl, blend Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in spinach and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Spread Ricotta mixture evenly on lasagna strips.
Roll up each strip.
Spread one third of sauce on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish to cover.
Place roll-ups seam-side down in sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot, 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: patio baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
In bacon drippings saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Return bacon to skillet.
Add beans. Stir in brown sugar, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix well, the soy sauce, sugar, mustard, horseradish and garlic powder.
Now add chicken wings and mix well.
Let stand overnight or several hours.
Bake on jelly roll pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: memaw's chili
directions: Brown ground beef in cooking oil; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: gazpacho (cold raw soup)
directions: Blend 1 tomato, 1/2 the onion, 1/2 the bell pepper, 1/2 cucumber, pimento and 1/2 cup tomato juice. Chop remaining 1 tomato, 1/2 the onion, 1/2 cucumber and 1/2 bell pepper.

title: grandma nita's homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and 2 Tbsp sugar and enough flour to make sponge (about 4 cups).
Cover and let rise, for 1 hour.
Add milk, egg, melted butter, remaining sugar and enough flour to make soft dough.
Mix well.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled in bulk - about 1-1/2 or 2 hours. Divide dough.
Roll out on floured board to about 1/4 inch thickness.

title: corned beef sandwich
directions: In a skillet on medium heat, mix oil and onion.
Brown onion. Add ketchup and mustard.
Stir.
Add crumbly corned beef.
Serve on warm buns with your favorite toppings.

title: jan witter's sour cream apple squares
directions: Blend flour, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts. Press 2 3/4 cups mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining mixture with the rest of ingredients.
Stir in chopped apples.
Spoon over crumble base.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or powdered sugar, if desired.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Mix together softened cheese spread, margarine and garlic powder.
Spread on both sides of bread slices and spread tops of loaves.
Then sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Wrap bread in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Make balls and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix pineapple with marshmallows and refrigerate overnight.
Heat juice, flour, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix apples, peanuts, pineapple and sauce.
Add Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients, flavoring and sour cream. Grease tube pan. Layer batter and cranberry sauce with sauce on top. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cool in pan 20 minutes.

title: no cook cream cheese fudge
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Slowly beat in sugar, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Press into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cherry dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Thaw orange juice and lemonade.
Combine with cranberry juice cocktail and water.
Chill or freeze to a slush consistency.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves 20 (1/2 cup) portions with 47 calories and 0 fat.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt; gradually add milk to mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake for 5 minutes.

title: deis fudge
directions: In large bowl, combine walnuts, butter or margarine, Nestle chips and vanilla; set aside.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk and marshmallows.
Bring to boil; boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over ingredients in bowl. Stir until dissolved.
Pour onto greased pan; allow to cool.
Cut into sizes of choice.

title: best beef burritos ever
directions: Fix the meat according to the directions on the burrito package.
Place prepared meat in the middle of a large flour tortilla.
Put a tablespoon of the enchilada sauce down the center of the burrito.
Place the desired amount of cheese on the meat. Fold the burrito shut and place in the microwave for 20 seconds, just enough time to slightly melt the cheese.
You can add just about anything you want.
Some suggestions are listed.

title: creamy key lime pie(from poogan's porch restaurant in charleston, south carolina)
directions: *Key lime juice is available in bottles in specialty food stores.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Drain green beans; add all ingredients and refrigerate well. Serve cold.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Beat together cake mix (dry), pudding and egg for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with chips, chopped pecans and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients and put in a large dish; freeze.
Keeps 4 to 6 weeks. Take out of the freezer at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed on cake mix package, except add 1 cup coconut to batter.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is hot, poke holes with a fork all over cake.
Pour liquid cream of coconut over the cake and allow to cool.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Beat together pistachio pudding and pineapple.
Fold marshmallows and Cool Whip or Dream Whip into mixture. Refrigerate in long glass dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top (optional).

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cocoa and 3/4 cup sugar in saucepan.
Blend in 2/3 cup evaporated milk and 1/2 cup light corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/3 cup butter or margarine and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: iron skillet chocolate icing
directions: In small bowl, mix together cocoa, sugar and salt.
Place eggs in skillet.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter, syrup and vanilla.
Turn heat to medium and slowly cook mixture, stirring constantly until it begins to boil and sugar is dissolved, (about 3 minutes).
Punch holes in cake of your choice and pour icing over it.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and canned milk.
Mix and stir in butter.
Last add coconut and nuts.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in two small loaf pans for 15 minutes at 350°, then for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in floured 1-pound coffee can at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes.
May be refrigerated for up to 10 days.

title: my mother's pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add karo and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans last and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes and reduce to 350 degrees for remainder of time.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1/2 large Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Layer bananas, pineapple and 1/2 large Cool Whip over the cream cheese mixture. Drizzle with chocolate and strawberry syrups.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: biscuits and sausage gravy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.

Add buttermilk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times. Roll dough to 3/4 inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Brush tops with butter.
Split biscuits open; serve with Sausage Gravy.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: confetti spread
directions: Combine chopped vegetables with remaining ingredients.
If dip needs more salt, adjust to taste.

title: chocolate chip marshmallow pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until melted.
Chill until partially set.
Fold into Cool Whip and chocolate.
Pile into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and let set.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Add dry ingredients to egg and mix well together.
Roll thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll and slice thin. Spread and let dry for 2 hours.
Drop in boiling broth and cook for 10 minutes.

title: fudge - five pounds
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk.
Boil exactly 9 minutes. Combine chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and butter (2 sticks) and vanilla.
Mix well and pour second mixture into first mixture.
Stir until chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour and cook for 1 minute. Gradually add milk.
Stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, 1/2 chives, half the bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Stir until heated.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Top individual servings with cheese, chives and bacon.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs. Add sugar and flour. Add corn. Add milk; mix thoroughly. Add salt and pepper. Put in greased medium casserole dish. Dot with margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Bake uncovered about 30 minutes, until set. Makes 6 servings.

title: sherried onions
directions: Simmer for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 2 quarts of water with 2 stalks celery, bay leaves, onion, 2 diced carrots and salt for about 1 1/2 hours. Cool the chicken; keep the broth, but throw away the vegetables. Boil 2 diced carrots, 2 diced stalks of celery and sliced mushrooms in broth for about 15 minutes.
Cube the chicken. Strain the broth, but keep the vegetables this time.

title: peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Sift flour, once measured.
Add baking soda and salt; sift together.
Mix butter with spoon, then add peanut butter.
Mix together.
Then add both sugars; mix well.
Add eggs and flour, a little at a time.
Form in quarter balls and smooth down with fork dipped into confectioners sugar.
Crisscross as you smash down. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes five dozen.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk.
Bring to boil.
Stir and boil over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.
Delicious!!

title: hot sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell.
Spread browned sausage in pie shell.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat together eggs and milk; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° until browned and bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add syrup and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts and mix.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set and lightly brown on top.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Blend honey and mustard together thoroughly.
Yields 1 quart.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mash and measure 1 cup.
Add egg to squash and mix well.
Add onion.
Combine dry ingredients and add to squash mixture.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fluffy peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray three 8-inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Prepare cake mix as label directed following no cholesterol recipe.
Spoon batter evenly into cake pans.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Remove cake from pans and cool completely.
Drain peach juice, coarsley chopped peaches to juice in bowl, add whipped topping, pudding mix and chopped peach, stirring gently.
Place cake on plate, spread with 3/4 cup mixture, then do the same to the second and third layer.
Use remaining mixture to frost side of cake.
Refrigerate.
(Contains 175 calories per slice; 4 grams fat; 0 cholesterol.)

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and add dressing before serving. Also, toss in one small bag of crushed Fritos.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion, hot sauce, sour cream and chopped chilies.
Spread thinly on tortillas; lay ham on top of spread.
Roll tortillas up tightly.
Chill.
When ready to serve, cut into bite size pinwheels.

title: sunrise cooler
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: "anginares me arni kai avgolemono" - lamb with artichokes and
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy; add flour, beating 1 minute longer.
Slowly add lemon juice and very slowly add all of the hot stock, beating constantly.
Pour egg-lemon mixture back into saucepan with lamb; shake saucepan back and froth to incorporate sauce with meat and artichokes.

title: pineapple macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add egg, then toss with Miracle Whip.

title: broccoli dip
directions: In saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Chop broccoli in small pieces.
Add to onion mixture with cheese spread, soup and seasonings.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with corn chips or vegetables.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate and margarine together; mix in the flour and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir as little as possible. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Put into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: In a deep pan or iron skillet place uncooked rice.
Place onions, parsley and celery on top of rice.
Pour tomato juice and water over rice.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue and ham
directions: Simmer 1/2 hour and then add 1 pound chipped ham.
Serve on buns.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables 20 minutes; drain.
Mix vegetables with onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in 2-quart baking dish. Mix crushed crackers with melted margarine and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: great cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In a 2-quart bowl, mix dry ingredients. Add egg and milk and stir until well moistened.
Place Crisco in a 9-inch Pyrex pie plate and heat until melted.
Raise sides to cover with Crisco.
Pour mix into dish and bake for 12 minutes. Remove and cut into slices.
Cornbread will be crispy.

title: low-fat potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, onions and carrots in a pan.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Leave water in pan.
Add fat free cheese and stir until cheese is melted.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except sausage in a boiler; bring to a boil.
Add sausage and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Measure salt and sugar into mixing bowl.
Add milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Crumble yeast into water.
When milk is lukewarm, add yeast mixture, eggs and about 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and knead into soft dough.
Place in warm, buttered bowl to rise 1 hour.
Working on a lightly floured board, cut dough into size of walnuts.
Form into balls.
Dip each into 1/2 cup melted butter, then roll in mixture of sugar, cinnamon and walnuts. Place layer of balls in a well-greased 9-inch tube pan so that they touch.
Sprinkle with raisins, pressing in lightly.
Add another layer of dough balls and another of raisins.
This will fill 2 (9-inch) pans.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done.
Invert pan to allow mixture to run down sides. Remove while warm.

title: easy drop rolls
directions: Combine ingredients, except flour.
Beat in flour until all is used up.
Dough will be sticky.
Put dough in large greased bowl. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Dip dough into greased muffin pan and let rise until twice the size.
Dough lasts about a week.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, milk, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add peaches.
Spray 9x13 inch pan with non stick spray.
Pour peach mixture into the prepared pan and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and mushrooms, then drain.
Add sour cream.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: salad for a crowd
directions: Break-up broccoli and cauliflower into florets; quarter tomatoes.
Combine all vegetables, cheese and bacon in a large bowl.
Combine salad dressings; pour over salad and toss to mix. Chill.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers until fine and pour milk over them.
Add nuts, cherries, cherry juice, raisins and marshmallows.
Mix well. Pour into container lined with waxed paper.
Pack until firm and store in refrigerator 1 week before cutting.

title: peanut butter potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add peanut butter. Mix. Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Dough will be somewhat stiff.
Blend in potato chips and walnuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and allow to cool on rack before storing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off top of bell peppers; remove seeds.
Precook peppers in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
(Omit precooking for crisper peppers.)
Sprinkle inside of peppers with salt.
Brown the ground beef and onion; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, rice, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Stuff the peppers with this mixture.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "miss" peggy's congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple and Jell-O (stir until dissolved).
Make sure mixture is good and hot all the way through.
Take off the stove and set on counter.
Let mixture cool completely.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash pintos.
Chop pecans.
Mix all the ingredients together. Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until pie crust browns.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Pinch the cake in pieces, then add drained pineapple, sliced bananas, sliced strawberries and Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour or overnight. Ready to serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add to cream mixture.
Place Cool Whip lid in bottom of plastic flowerpot.
Layer cookies and cream mixture, beginning and ending with cookies.
Garnish with gummy worms and silk flowers. Serve with dirt scoop, if desired.

title: spiced punch(recipe from old virginia)
directions: Pour 10 cups boiling water over tea leaves.
Steep 4 minutes. Strain; add other ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Start layering with lettuce.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and peas.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Spread crescent rolls onto a pizza pan.
Sprinkle sausage onto the crescent rolls.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Add onions.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over everything.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 12 cup muffin tin.
Mix oil, molasses and squash puree.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir together wet and dry ingredients and raisins.
Drop into muffin cups and bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: easy flavored syrup
directions: In saucepan, heat on medium heat until smooth.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.
Baking time may vary, depending on the size of the dish used.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine soup and seasoning package from rice and heat.
Place rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 soup mixture. Place chicken breasts on top and cover with remaining soup. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and slivered almonds.
Cover and bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour to brown.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture.
Mix and chill. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies.
Mix pudding and pour over.
Slice bananas and strawberries; layer over pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: pistachio nut dessert
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl. Cover.
Let set overnight.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Mix water and jello with electric mixer.
Add sugar, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Add pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Put in freezer; let set until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk together. Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Hush puppies should flip the first time on their own.

title: jailhouse rolls(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Blend potatoes, margarine, eggs, salt and sugar.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Finally, add yeast water to this mixture.
Place in a large covered bowl and refrigerate for several hours.
Three hours before dinner, take as much dough as needed and roll it out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a glass dipped in flour and arrange side by side in a slightly greased baking dish.
Butter tops lightly. Allow to stand on open countertop for 3 hours to rise.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate dipped delights
directions: Insert long wooden picks into fruit to be dipped.
Dip fruit, nuts or pretzels into chocolate, covering at least half.
Let excess chocolate drip off.
Sprinkle with colored sprinkles, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with Cool Whip.
Place in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Cover tightly and place in freezer overnight. Serve frozen.

title: cheese and onion caps
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until thoroughly blended. Season with 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Press into caps.
Place on greased broiler pan, about 4 inches from heat, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Do not overbroil.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl and then put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add another 1/4 cup melted margarine (or butter) and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in chocolate and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with an electric mixer at medium speed for 5 minutes after each addition. Turn into pastry shell. Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: banana-nut party cake
directions: Cream sugar with shortening until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt together; beat into egg mixture.
Add soda to buttermilk; blend well.
Add buttermilk and bananas to flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and fruit.
Turn into greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: kindergarten french fries
directions: Take a package of French fries.
Put in grease.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in large frypan.
Add fresh garlic. Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Brown chicken quickly to a lovely color (this is not to cook chicken, only to brown and seal). When browned to golden color, remove chicken and place in baking dish.

title: barley casserole
directions: Brown onions and barley in margarine.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Put in casserole, cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kraut
directions: Mix together.
Let set 1 hour and pack in jars and seal.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; save 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice.
Cut peaches into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine fruit, marshmallows and ginger. Soften gelatin with cold water.
Heat pineapple juice to boiling. Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Add orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.
Chill.
When mixture starts to thicken, add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Spoon into quart milk cartons or other containers. Cover and freeze for at least 1 1/2 days.
Remove as much as you need.
Slice and serve.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, vinegar, and sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil, and then add liquid pectin.
Bring back to boil; let boil three to four minutes longer.
Add a few drops of food coloring for color desired.	Take off heat; continue to stir for several minutes longer.
Seal in pint size sterile jars.

title: jerica's salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Boil eggs until done.
Rinse and cut lettuce with your desire of cutting.
Take bacon, crunch and break into bits.
Dice chicken breast slices.
(Drain grease from bacon.)
Mix the 2 meats in bowl together; set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Cook until thick, then add Jell-O and lemon juice.
Cool, then pour over strawberries in cooked pie shell.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make a cup and add to gelatin.
Add berries and crushed pineapple to mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over congealed gelatin. Sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate.
