title: spicy potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion mix and butter.
Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil
chicken
breasts
for 1 hour to make a good stock. Remove
and
debone.
Set
aside.
Boil
rice
in chicken stock according to package measurements.
Add soup, chicken, salt and pepper
to
taste and mix well.
Bake in conventional 350° oven for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: my favorite casserole
directions: Combine all leftovers from the left side of the refrigerator. Top with Herr's potato chips; bake.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage together and mix with Bisquick.
Shape into balls.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: taco spread
directions: Place on platter in the order listed.
Serve with plain Tostitos.

title: beef taco enchiladas
directions: Roll boneless breasts in sour cream until coated.
Crush potato chips and roll chicken in chips.
Place chicken in greased flat baking dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter per breast.
Crush medium clove of garlic and mix with butter.
Drizzle over chicken. Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill several hours.
At serving time, slowly pour in ginger ale.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Place softened butter and cream cheese in a blender or food processor.
Add herbs and mix well.
Spoon into mold or bowl and chill.
Serve with crackers.
Keeps in refrigerator 2 weeks or may be frozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a lightly greased large pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Have Bundt pan sprayed with Pam and hot. Pour cake mixture into hot pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool. Top with powdered sugar if desired.

title: pralines - pecan
directions: Mix sugar, soda, milk and Karo in a 2-quart boiler and let reach soft ball.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until shiny or thick enough to drop from teaspoons.
Add pecans and drop on waxed paper.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cut mushrooms into small pieces.
Add mushrooms, 1 cup water, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes with carrots.
Add beef bouillon cubes, 2 cups water and milk.
Thicken with flour.
Just before serving, add evaporated milk.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift and mix together the flour, brown sugar, soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and baking powder.
Make hole in dry ingredients.
Combine olive oil, pumpkin, water and eggs; mix and add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes for loaves. Makes 2 dozen muffins or 3 medium loaves.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, tossing to coat apples. Place in a 2-quart baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and wheat germ; cut in butter with
a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in oil and pecans and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar and baking powder.
Beat in vanilla.
Mix nuts with crushed crackers.
Gently fold into meringue mixture.
Grease a 9-inch glass pie plate well. Spread mixture in plate. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool completely.
Whip the cream and vanilla. Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: 24 hour 7-layer salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl (with cover) in the following order: lettuce, torn in bite size pieces, celery, carrots, green peas, pepper and onions.
Frost with mayonnaise
mixed with sugar.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Do not mix.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pastry shell in very hot oven (450°) only 7 minutes, or just until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble and reserve 2 tablespoons of the bacon bits.
Place remaining bacon in pie shell; add cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Trim with reserved bacon.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until almost set in center.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, let cool.
Cut up salami, pepperoni and Provolone cheese.
Chop onion, peppers, celery and tomatoes.
Add all these ingredients to macaroni.
Add olives and spices.
When well mixed, add oil and vinegar, preferably just before serving.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Saute meat in shortening.
Add other ingredients and cook in covered skillet for about 30 minutes or bake in covered casserole at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or on buns.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken breasts.
Drain and wipe dry with paper towels. Dip in 100% corn oil and then in crushed cornflakes.
Place in buttered cake pan.
Pour oil over top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
(I use No-Salt from grocery store.)
Bake 1 hour or longer, if not tender.
Serve.

title: broccoli and cauliflower pizza
directions: Cut up fresh broccoli and cauliflower.
Bake crescent roll, rolled out onto 9x13 pan.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and ranch dressing.
Spread mixture onto cooled crescent rolls.
Top with broccoli and cauliflower and cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of water until tender; drain. In a sauce pan combine butter and sugar; heat until sugar is melted.
Add carrots and turn to coat; heat though.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and green pepper in a large bowl. Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Pickles will last several weeks.

title: diabetic gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Beat in yogurt until blended.
Add vinegar and chopped apricot halves.
Chill until firm.
Spread a thin coating of salad dressing over jello. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pickled okra
directions: Place one hot pepper and one garlic clove in each hot sterilized jar. Remove part of stem from each okra pod. Pack okra into jars and add one teaspoon of dill seed to each jar.

title: lucile's brownies
directions: Blend stick margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar to eggs and combine chocolate mixture.
Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased pan that has been dusted with cocoa or flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling.
Add noodles and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Mix egg and flavorings. Stir dry ingredients together and blend mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Roll and cut. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown orzo in melted butter and then instantly stir in 1 cup rice.
Add water and bring to a boil (add salt and bouillon also). Cover after it begins to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Turn off and let stand (covered) for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients with 4 cups self-rising flour.
Knead in 1 1/2 to 2 cups more self-rising flour.
(Can be made out into rolls or placed in refrigerator at this point.)
Make out into rolls and let rise in pan for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: wayne's chili
directions: In a large pot cook ground meat.
Drain well.
Add tomato juice, chopped onions, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste. Cook for about 1 hour on low heat.
Chili beans may be added.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine Karo and sugar in a large pan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Stir.
Pour in Rice Krispies and mix until coated.
Dump in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Pour over top of the Rice Krispies; spread evenly.
Let topping sit, then cut into bars.
Makes 28 to 32 bars per pan.
Enjoy!

title: k. c. baked beans
directions: Stir together first eight ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish; top with bacon.

title: greek spinach bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart shallow casserole or baking dish.
Beat eggs in medium-size bowl until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into casserole.
Bake 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: fresh candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes whole until done.
Cook the sugar in small pan until forms ball or thickens.
Peel potatoes.
Cut up in long pan. Pour sugar over them.
Cover well; sprinkle the cinnamon, brown sugar and raisins over top.
Don't burn the raisins!
Serve hot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add milk, egg, corn, jalapenos and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: jalapeno coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed; mix well.
Sprinkle pepper on top, if desired.
Chill before serving.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt margarine.
Mix into a large ball.
Pinch off into small pieces and roll into balls and place on wax paper.

title: best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend cornstarch, 1 1/2 cups sugar and salt in medium saucepan. Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir 1/2 mixture into egg yolks.
Stir into mixture remaining in saucepan. Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon peel and juice.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked crust.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or meringue lightly brown.

title: klivan's cranberry hazelnut pie
directions: In a bowl beat eggs and add brown sugar.
Stir in maple syrup, butter, salt and vanilla, then add nuts and cranberries.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly, add eggs one at a time beating well after each. Alternately add the liquid with the dry ingredients, beginning and ending with flour. Sift 1/4 cup flour over the fruit and nuts. Mix this in dough. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes in 300 degree preheated oven.

title: pot buster beans
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onions; drain and put into crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low or 1 hour on high.
Can be cooked in regular pot about 1 hour.
Stir frequently.

title: ham slices with apple rings
directions: Cut ham slices in half.
Cover with boiling water and boil for 8 minutes.
Drain and place in shallow baking dish.
Cover ham with brown sugar.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top and cover with pineapple juice.
Bake, uncovered, in an oven preheated to 350° for 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Cut apples into slices and saute in butter until brown and serve over ham.

title: brownies
directions: Mix with spoon until bubbles form.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh fruit with custard sauce
directions: Mix in a pan the first 4 ingredients.
Slowly add 3/4 cup and 2 tablespoons of milk.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in 3 tablespoons of the hot mixture.
Gradually add egg mixture to mixture in pan, stirring constantly.
Heat until almost boiling. Cool slightly.
Add fresh fruit.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix together rhubarb, white sugar and 3 tablespoons flour. Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine and 1 1/2 cups flour and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar and continue beating until it stands in peaks.
Add strawberries.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Flavor with vanilla; use enough flour so soft dough can be rolled out and cut.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut in cubes.
Put half of cubes in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add cheese, then remaining cubes. Add mixture of milk, beaten eggs and salt (pour evenly over bread and cheese).
Pour melted butter over top.
Add paprika.
Keep covered overnight in refrigerator.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Toss potato slices in egg whites.
Sprinkle with desired seasoning and toss to coat.
Spray pan with nonstick spray and place potatoes into pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Boil the
butter, sugar and milk together in a saucepan for 2 minutes.
Remove
from
heat
and stir in the chocolate chips, stirring until melted.

title: orange cupcakes(makes 50 small)
directions: Beat the eggs together. Stir in the sugar and flour.
Mix together.
Heat the milk, butter and pinch
of salt. Add to milk mixture the vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour melted butter and milk into egg mixture, beating constantly. Stir in the baking powder before baking. Fill muffin pans not more than half full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dilled zucchini and leek soup
directions: In kettle over medium high heat, cook the zucchini and the leeks in the drippings or oil for about 7 minutes, or until tender.
Add broth and spices.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Allow soup to cool slightly, then puree (in batches) in blender or food processor.
Ladle the soup, reheated if necessary, into heated bowls.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash sweet
potatoes;
add eggs and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add all other ingredients; mix until
well
blended.
Pour
into
a large casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Make topping.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Trim excess fat from venison.
In large bowl, mix beer, garlic,
salt, pepper, onions and
bay
leaves.
Add
venison. Marinate in refrigerator for 12 to 14 hours, turning occasionally. Remove venison and onions	from
marinade	and place in crock-pot.	Pour 1 cup barbecue sauce over venison.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 10 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in warm water.
Mix altogether.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Ice with sour cream frosting.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, sugar, jello and buttermilk; mix well.
Add flour to egg mixture and blend, then add drained strawberries and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 15 minutes.
Use only enough Miracle Whip to coat other ingredients.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook roast until done.
Pull apart into small pieces.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns with coleslaw.

title: grape velvet
directions: Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons crumbs in bottom of 8 dessert dishes.
Reserve remaining crumbs.
In a small mixing bowl cream together butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Drop a spoonful of creamed mixture onto crumb base, dividing equally.
Top with bananas and grapes, reserving a few grapes for garnish.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with reserved grapes and crumbs.
Chill 1 hour.

title: apple pie slices
directions: Cover the bottom of a standard size cookie sheet with pie crust.
Add apple pie filling.
Spread evenly over the pie crust. Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon to taste. Use the remaining pie crusts to cover.
Poke holes in top of crust and seal edges.
Bake at 350° as you would for a pie, until done. When cooled completely, frost with powdered sugar icing of slightly runny, but not glaze consistency.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix egg yolks well with fork.
Slowly add cooking oil, stirring each time until blended; when amount needed is reached, add dash of mustard or lemon juice to congeal.
Salt and pepper.

title: grandma kurpjuwert's raw apple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in an 11 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.

title: four cheese chicken and pasta
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
In skillet, brown chicken; drain.
Add tomatoes; cook, uncovered, until slightly thickened. Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss with remaining ingredients. Cover 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Can add a little salsa to make it spicy.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat slowly in chafing dish and serve with bread cubes.

title: russian stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in oil; set aside.
Cut vegetarian steak in long finger-like strips and dip in brewer's yeast.
Stew chunks could be dipped in brewer's yeast also.
If using hamburger, brown and drain off fat.
Add onions, steak or hamburger, mushrooms (juice from mushrooms and steak) and mushroom soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: zucchini and sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Stir in soup, broth, seasoning and zucchini.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add rice and stir gently.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings.
Mix flour and salt and then add to mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Blend red coloring in half.
Roll 1 teaspoon each color on floured board, 4-inches long.
Press strips together and twist like rope and curve like cane.
Bake on ungreased baking pan for 9 minutes or until light brown.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put eggs, vinegar and sugar in top of double boiler.
Put pan over simmering water and beat mixture constantly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat, add butter, then cool.
When cold, fold in whipped cream, marshmallows and fruit mixture.
Turn into fancy glass dish.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chili chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook and stir onion in butter until tender; stir in soup, pimento and chili pepper.
In greased 4-quart casserole, layer half the noodles and half the chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Top with half the soup mixture and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers and remove seeds.
Precook peppers in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit boiling.)
Sprinkle inside of peppers with a little salt.
Brown meat with onion.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, 1/2 cup water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chili pie
directions: Layer 2 cups corn chips, onion, 1/2 cup cheese and preheated chili in 1-quart casserole. Top with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Brown ground beef in large skillet and drain.
Return beef back to skillet and add taco seasoning mix, tomatoes and corn.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into prepared dish.
Beat the egg in separate bowl; add milk and cornbread mix.
Stir until smooth.
Pour cornbread batter over ground beef mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: john's poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in 1 cup milk for 1 hour.
Cream oleo and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add cake flour and baking powder and fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon almond extract.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Brown chicken in butter until golden.
Arrange chicken in casserole dish.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove onion with cloves and bay leaf.
Mix butter and flour and drop by bits into casserole, stirring well as you go.
Add cream, mushrooms and thyme.
Bake 15 more minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve.

title: dried fruit fried pies
directions: Combine flour and
salt,
cut
in
oleo
and shortening until mixture is	uniform.
Add flavoring and food coloring to cold water.
Then mix
with
the
beaten egg.
Cut dough while preparing
the
filling.
Roll
dough
approximately
1/8-inch thick, cut into 3-inch squares and fold into triangles.
Place 1 tablespoon of dried
fruit into center of square and smooth. Moisten edge with water,
fold over to pinch sides with a fork and seal.
Fry	in
deep
approximately 2 minutes. Drain well on paper towels.

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: Mix and cover; refrigerate at least 45 minutes, stirring several times.

title: brownies
directions: Mix caramels with 1/2 cup cream in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until melted and mixed.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix cake.
Mix 3/4 cup butter and cream.
It will be stiff.
(You may add 1 small can of cream - optional.) Spread 1/2 of cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips and cover with cool caramel mixture.
Last, top with rest of cake mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 more minutes.

title: easy microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat with onion and seasonings.
Chop so it's fine. Clean peppers and cut in half lengthwise.
Add corn to meat.
Fill peppers and put in oblong dish.
Dilute tomato soup and pour over top.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes on High power until peppers are soft.

title: taco chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass baking dish in single layer.
Shake taco seasoning over chicken.
Cover with clear wrap or wax paper and cook in microwave, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:

one cup sauce, noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce, all Ricotta cheese, 1/3 Mozzarella, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce, all of cream cheese, 1/3 Mozzarella, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, noodles, 1 cup sauce, 1/3 Mozzarella and 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: "mother adams" homemade noodles
directions: In mixing bowl, make nest in center; add eggs and salt.
You can stir or mix eggs and salt together before adding.

Make a stiff dough, gradually working in flour, like you would making biscuits. Lift dough onto a floured surface and continue to work in flour as long as needed; roll out dough until it is very thin. Let set 20 to 30 minutes. Roll up and with a sharp knife, cut 1/8 inch strips, starting at one end of the roll. This makes enough for 2 meals for a small family. Allow the extra noodles to dry completely and store in a covered jar until needed. Drop the (two day) noodles into boiling broth (chicken or beef) and cook for about 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with no-stick cooking spray. Place crescent rolls flat in bottom of dish. Sprinkle with sausage. Beat eggs; salt and pepper to taste. Pour over sausage and sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Check eggs for doneness.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Whisk together soup and milk in large mixing bowl. Whisk in Alfredo sauce. Stir in chopped turkey, next 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Pour into a lightly greased 15 x 10-inch baking dish.

title: aunt becky's chopped liver
directions: In a large skillet with 1/2 stick margarine, cook liver until done.
Remove to platter.
Slice onions and saute in same skillet until done; add remaining margarine as needed.
Onions should be cooked until browned.
Cook eggs until hard-boiled; drain, shell and cool.
Chop liver with chopping machine or chopping bowl. Transfer liver to large mixing bowl, then chop hard-boiled eggs and onions.
Add to liver mixture; mix all ingredients.
Add seasonings and mayonnaise to moisten and to taste.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes to mix. Place in a greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix together the jello, cheese and water; put on stove and boil for 10 minutes, or until cream cheese is melted.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix; put in refrigerator.

title: chess cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan. Mix 1 box yellow cake mix, 1 stick margarine, and egg. Put on bottom of pan and pat down a little. Mix together 3 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour over top and bake at 375 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes (knife will come out mostly clean).

title: meat balls teriyaki
directions: Cut garlic in 4 pieces.
Saute in oil over very low heat, being careful not to brown garlic.
Remove and discard.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add browned meat balls and cook over low heat until meat balls absorb most of the sauce. Serve as hot hors d'oeuvre.
Yields enough sauce for 4 dozen bite-size meat balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take cooked chicken and shred in bottom of casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream together, then pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and add poppy seed and cracker crumbs.
Pour over soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake at 400° until it starts to bubble and topping browns, about 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad(fluff)
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple; refrigerate 2 hours.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: black raspberry ice cream
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat egg until light.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir in cream, pudding mix, vanilla and a dash of salt. Pour into a 4 to 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Stir in milk and raspberries.
Follow freezer instructions to freeze.
Ripen. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
This is good stuff.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in large frying pan.
Drain grease.
Mix in refried beans.
Heat, covered, on medium 5 minutes.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer ingredients into dish as follows:

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Then beat in the egg and vanilla. In a separate bowl, combine the flour and salt, then mix with the butter/egg/sugar mixture.
Chill the dough for 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
On a flour-covered surface, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake cookies on a greased cookie sheet for about 8 minutes.

title: blueberry icebox cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and oleo together and press into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Blend eggs, sugar and cream cheese well with mixer and spread on cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add juice from 1 lemon to pie mix.
Mix well and add to baked crust.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown sausage, then crumble.
Drain off grease.
Saute onion in margarine, then stir in soup, Cheez Whiz and broccoli until smooth.
Mix rice, sausage and Cheez mixture.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Beat together eggs, buttermilk, melted butter, molasses, vanilla, sugar and pumpkin in a large bowl. Stir in dry ingredients all at once.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Spoon into cups. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup, water and salt until dissolved.
Boil to medium ball stage (240°).
Pour slowly 1/3 of hot mixture over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to 265°.
Beat syrup into candy mixture.
When mixture holds shape, add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper. (Any food coloring can be used.)
Add pecans when candy loses shine.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in a small saucepan. Beat eggs and add sugar.
Add melted chocolate and butter to the egg and sugar mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Could add 3/4 cup pecans if you would like!

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Put fruit into baked pie shell.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, water, white karo and salt until transparent.
Add Jell-O.
Remove from heat and let set until mixture gels.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash and onions together.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
In saucepan, add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; add squash and onions.
Boil until it turns pink.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: rich chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together; dough will be stiff.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes for a chewy, rich cookie.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Note:
Velveeta cheese can be used for the package cheese spread.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine and combine with graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into 11 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: delia's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and jar up.
Keep jar in refrigerator and add beer only in the amount that you are using at any given time.

title: hamburger green bean casserole
directions: Add 1 can drained green beans, 1 can tomato soup and 1/2 can water; simmer.
While meat is simmering, peel and boil potatoes. Drain and mash with butter and 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Pour meat mixture into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with spoonfuls of potato and cheese mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. chapman's pickled beets
directions: Cook on top of stove 5 minutes.
Makes 2 cans of beets.

title: kourambiedes(christmas)
directions: This is a healthier version of a regular pumpkin cheesecake.
I served it at Thanksgiving, but didn't say it was made from tofu until after we ate it.
No one could believe it!
They loved it!

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir and cook sugar, corn syrup, whipping cream and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until syrup boils a brittle boil; pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well.
Grease hands and shape into balls.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken a l'orange 2
directions: Remove excess fat and skin from chicken.
Wash and put in roasting pan.
Mix onion soup and defrosted orange juice in bowl. Spoon mixture thickly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. If not brown on top, put under broiler for 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve with rice and vegetable.
Dilute leftover orange mixture and use as sauce on chicken and rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: mama's gingerbread
directions: Mix and sift first 4 ingredients.
Blend Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add molasses and blend well.
Add next 2 ingredients and slowly add dry ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) cake pan.

title: quick fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered pan. Then let stand for thirty minutes in refrigerator. Then cut and serve.
Hmm Hmm Good Good!!!

title: pineapple-cherry crisp
directions: In medium saucepan, combine drained cherries, undrained pineapple, granulated sugar, quick-cooking tapioca, lemon juice and red food coloring.
Let stand 15 minutes; cook and stir until thickened and clear, 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and salt. Add eggs one at a time while mixing.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let chill for awhile.

title: potatoes savoyarde
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart gratin or baking dish.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/8-inch thin slices.
Spread half of them in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with half the salt and pepper.
Cut butter into small pieces and dot top of potatoes with half the butter.
Add the rest of the potatoes, salt, pepper and butter.
Top with the cheese.
Pour in stock.
Bake until golden and bubbly, about 40 minutes.
Let potatoes stand 10 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Add enough white flour to make a dough that can be kneaded.
Allow to rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Shape into 3 or 4 loaves.
Let rise again. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
If loaves become too dark, reduce oven temperature near end of baking period.

title: potato puffs
directions: In a mixing bowl beat egg yolks.
Add potatoes, Parmesan cheese, parsley, onion and garlic powder; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into the potato mixture.
Brush eight muffin cups generously with melted butter.
Divide potato mixture into cups.
Brush remaining butter over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook ground beef, green peppers and onions until browned. Add soups and spices. Boil noodles until tender. Drain noodles and stir with beef and soup mixture. Place in baking dish and top with slices of cheese. Bake at 350 degree in oven until cheese melts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour and stir to paste.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese, soup and salt.
Place beans in buttered casserole.
Pour sauce over beans.
Stir gently. Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Add pimento.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bessie's pickled eggs
directions: Hard-boil and peel eggs.
Prick each one several times with a fork.
Place in a large stoneware crock or a deep bowl.
Heat together in a separate pan, but do not boil, the beets, vinegar, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour hot mixture over the eggs and cool. Cover and store in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: pralines
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, milk and butter in pan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves; then cook without stirring until a soft ball will form when dropped in a cup of cold water.

title: potato candy
directions: Cut up potato. Cook until it is tender; drain. Put in bowl and let cool. Mash up potato. Add sugar until it resembles play dough. Roll out to 1/4-inch thick. Spread on peanut butter. Roll up like a jelly roll. Cut into 1/4-inch pieces. Let dry. Put in layers with foil between in closed containers. The candy will last for 2 weeks.

title: lucille's lemon freeze
directions: Mash together the graham crackers and melted margarine and pat into a pie pan.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; brown.
Brown onion and garlic; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pan.
Add chicken to sauce and cover.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir.
Add water, if needed.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating until light.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Fill paper bake cups in muffin pans half full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with peanut butter.
Yield:
2 dozen cupcakes.

title: eggplant-ranch style
directions: Fry onion until soft. Add all other ingredients and cook until done (about 30 minutes). Sprinkle cheese over top when done.

title: gar's eye of round
directions: Great for serving large groups.
Can be cooked 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on box.
Remove from oven.
While hot, punch small holes in top of cake with fork.
Place pineapple with juice and sugar in small saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour this mixture over cake; mix vanilla instant pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pineapple mixture.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an oblong baking dish.
While this is melting in oven, mix together flour and sugar; add milk.
Pour this mixture into baking dish.
Spoon peaches over the top and add all the juice.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken stock with onion until soft.
Make roux with butter and flour.
Add broccoli and stock to roux.
Add half and half cream to mixture until desired consistency.
Heat thoroughly.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple jelly pork roast
directions: Rub roast well with salt, garlic and chili powder.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Roast at 325° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan, simmer for 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over roast, continue roasting, basting occasionally, until meat thermometer registers 155° to 160°, about 20 to 30 minutes. Remove roast from pan.
Rest for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove pan drippings to saucepan.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil.
Carve roast and serve with sauce.

title: apple pie yams
directions: Drain yams well.
Butter casserole dish and add yams and apple pie filling.
Mix well.
Put pats of butter on top and bake until well heated.

title: banana bread
directions: Put all ingredients, except walnuts, into a bowl; beat 3 minutes.
Add walnuts and mix well.
Pour into greased bread pan, 5 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches, spreading batter very high on the sides and low in the middle.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Serve sliced thin with butter or cream cheese.

title: orange whip
directions: Sprinkle orange gelatin into cottage cheese. Stir.
Mix in fruits.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: friendship bread starter(10 day bread)
directions: Starter:
Mix yeast and water.	Add flour and sugar.
Pour into one gallon ziploc bag.
Keep in a cool place.
DO NOT REFRIGERATE.

title: grannie's divinity
directions: Cook the sugar, syrup and water in a large bowl in microwave on High 12 minutes and 15 seconds. While this is cooking, beat your egg whites until stiff.
Pour this over your beaten egg whites and beat until stiff.
The trick is beat long enough before taking the beaters out.
Then fold in with a wooden spoon the vanilla and nuts.
Drop with teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cook beets until tender.
Peel.
Pack in jars.
Add syrup and seal.

title: spicy sunshine carrots
directions: Place in a 2-quart saucepan butter, all 3 juices, mustard, ginger, cinnamon, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Mix cornstarch and water until creamy; add to juices while bubbling. Stir constantly. Reduce heat to low and add carrots. Remove from heat when sauce is thickened. Serves 4.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Slice vegetables and chop onion. Saute vegetables and onion in butter until tender.
In a large Corning Ware casserole, put in vegetables.
Mix milk with soup and pour over top. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed on package.
Beat egg into stuffing and place on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes, until bubbly. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pastry recipe
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg yolk and milk; add to flour mixture.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Divide dough in half and roll for pies.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Add egg yolks to stiffly beaten egg whites and gradually add flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add hot milk very slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in layer cake pan 35 minutes at 350°.
When cool, split and put between layers Cream Filling.

title: overnite gooey ring
directions: Butter tube pan well.
Sprinkle pecans in pan.
Place whole bag of frozen rolls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle pudding mix on top.
Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon together.
Do not let it get thick.
Pour over rolls.
Don't cover pan.
Let sit on counter overnight.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Take out of pan immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: ham broccoli soup
directions: Mix together.
Bring to a light boil.
Cook on low for about 10 minutes.
Good with cornbread.

title: chef's salad
directions: Tear greens in bite size pieces into 4 salad bowls.
Layer atop each bowl, 1/4 of the ham and cheese strips, 2 cherry tomatoes (halved), 4 egg quarters and 1 tablespoon dressing. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: sinful chicken
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken in margarine.
Place a slice of cheese on each piece of chicken. Cover with 2 cans of undiluted soup.
Sprinkle 3 or 4 cups stuffing mix on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben in a dish
directions: Layer the above ingredients in a lasagna dish as follows: sauerkraut on bottom, then corned beef. Next, spread on the Thousand Island dressing, then place the Swiss cheese over the entire dish. Finish with rye bread which has been cut in squares or cubes and tossed with butter. Gently press down on top layer to make contact with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease 8-inch pan.
Melt shortening and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and add milk, egg and shortening.
Mix well until mixture is thin.
If not, add enough milk to make that way.
Place in greased pan and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
It should be very tall.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Brown meat quickly.
Add water and mushrooms (liquid, too).
Stir in soup mix; cook until meat is tender.
Blend flour into sour cream and add to meat mixture.
Stir until sauce thickens, but not to boiling.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Thaw and mash berries. Add eggs, sugar and oil; beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to mixture. Stir in pecans and butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Mix all in bowl.
Roll teaspoonful of dough in powdered sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to15 minutes.

title: hearty salad
directions: Layer 12 ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Toss and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 main servings or 10 to 12 salad servings.

title: bow tie pasta with sausage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add sausage and red pepper; cook. Then add onion and garlic; saute until tender (about 7 minutes). Add tomatoes, salt and cream.
Simmer 4 minutes until slightly thick.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Add parsley and Parmesan cheese to taste.
Great side dish or main dish.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine and oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Wash, salt, pepper and flour chicken pieces.
Place chicken in pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and bake another 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
(Do not cover chicken.)
Remove chicken from pan and make gravy with drippings.

title: lemon-rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rosemary and garlic.
Flatten chicken breast with palm of hand or back of a knife.
Arrange them on large sheet of foil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle rosemary-garlic mixture over chicken.
Slice lemons.
Put 2 to 3 slices on each breast.
Dot with butter.
Seal foil into packet. Place on baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: burritos
directions: Crumble pork sausage into 4 cup measure.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) until very little pink remains, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes; break up and drain.
Stir in bean dip, taco sauce, chili powder, garlic and salt.
Cover loosely and microwave until hot and bubbly, 2 to 3 1/2 minutes; stir.
Cover to keep warm.
Wrap tortillas in damp cloth and microwave on High (100%) until softened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread about 1/3 cup filling on each tortilla (keep remaining tortillas covered to prevent them from drying out); sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Fold sides over and roll from bottom.
Arrange burritos, seam sides down, forming a square on plate.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) until hot, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce if desired.

title: country club crisps
directions: Cut bacon into 2-inch strips.
Place strips on broiling pan. Broil one side until brown.
Remove from oven; flip strips and generously sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Broil until done and remove carefully.
Serve warm.

title: lynne toth's flying taco appetizer
directions: Spread refried beans in dish or pan. Mix seasonings with sour cream. Spread on beans. Add the rest.

title: apple palion
directions: Place
the
apple slices in a pie dish.
Cover with the sugar. Sprinkle over this a mixture of the remaining ingredients,
which have
been
blended
like	cornmeal.
Bake
in a moderate	(350°) oven for 40 minutes, or until the apples are tender.

title: mexican salad
directions: In a double boiler, melt cheese and drained Ro-Tel tomatoes. In skillet, brown hamburger; drain, if necessary.
Add taco mix. Put lettuce in a large bowl; add hamburger mix.
Add cheese-tomato mix and add Fritos.
Mix all together when ready to eat.

title: rabbit barbecue(depression barbecue)
directions: Brown rabbit and place into crock-pot with remaining items. Cook until desired doneness is reached or 2 hours on high.

title: tuna casserole poulet de la mer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup, sour cream, mushrooms, tuna fish and spices.
Add noodles, peas and carrots.
Melt butter; pour over croutons.
Sprinkle croutons over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve over low heat water, jello, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Add the other ingredients.
Pour into bowl.
Chill to set.
Recipe is easily doubled.

title: smoked turkey breast
directions: Clean, rinse and pat dry the turkey breast.
Be sure it is thawed.
Place in Brown-in-Bag with other ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Arrange eggs in medium saucepan.
Add cold water to cover 1-inch above eggs.
Bring to boil.
Cover; remove from heat. Allow to stand for 20 minutes.
Plunge eggs into cold water immediately; crack and remove shells.
Cut cooled eggs in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove yolks into small mixing bowl.
Mash yolks with remaining ingredients; season to taste.
Pile mixture back into egg halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken in water with the celery.
Take off the bone. In 9 x 13-inch pan layer chicken, broccoli and cheese, repeating layers.
Pour soup over mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chili eggs
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, beat eggs; add all other ingredients and stir.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: tuna spread
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatine and cream cheese.
Add tuna, celery, onion and Miracle Whip.
Put in a greased Bundt pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: swiss montana steak
directions: Combine seasonings.
Pound into meat.
Brown meat in shortening on both sides.
Place meat in large casserole pan, add all vegetables and sprinkle with worcestershire sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Steak will be very tender.

title: orange sesame seed cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour, sugar, sesame seed and orange peel.
Stir in orange juice and shortening; knead to form a soft dough.
On a lightly floured board, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness with a lightly floured rolling pin.
Cut dough into 3 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch rectangles.
Make a lengthwise slit in the center of each and bring one end through center to make a twist.

title: stuffed peppers sicilian
directions: Slice tops from peppers; chop tops and reserve.
Scoop out seeds and membrane from peppers.
In skillet cook onion, reserved green peppers, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add meat; cook until browned.
Spoon off excess fat.
Stir in tomato puree, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle salt inside pepper shells. Spoon meat mixture into the peppers.
Sprinkle cheese over filling.
Place in small baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 servings, 169 calories per serving.

title: cranberry fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and chill. Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 1 cup.

title: potato
directions: Dice raw potatoes; roll in a dish of corn meal seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in hot grease.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft).
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until solid.
Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Prepare egg noodles but leave slightly firm.
In large mixing bowl, combine noodles, tuna (drained and rinsed), soup and peas. Pour mixture into baking dish; bake at 350° until bubbling.
Let set until solid.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chopped pecans and coconut; spread over pan.
Mix cake mix by box directions and pour over nuts and coconut mixture.
Melt oleo.
Mix oleo, powdered sugar and softened cream cheese; pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: self-filled cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon flavoring and flour, a little at a time.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Mark off 24 squares.

title: tricia(liverwurst ball)
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball.
Spread the 1/4 you saved over it. Chill.
Serve.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Layer of pound cake, sliced thin.

title: brandied sweet potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes, unpeeled, until barely soft, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Arrange slices in a greased glass baking dish (don't stack them).

title: aunt ellen's meat casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in casserole.
Crush 1 tube of Ritz crackers, pour 1 stick melted oleo over them; bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Bake 20 minutes, then add cracker crumbs.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: corned beef and cheese spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with cold milk; beat until fluffy. Add diced meat and onions.
Beat again.
Great on crackers or cocktail rye.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant vanilla pudding according to package directions using 3 cups cold milk and sour cream.
After pudding has thickened, fold in Cool Whip.
In large bowl, make layers of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Garnish with wafer crumbs.

title: green bean and mushroom fricassee(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the green beans and carrots and cook until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towels.

title: irish coffee
directions: Put the whiskey into a stemmed Irish coffee glass or a mug. Fill with coffee. Stir in Splenda and top with whipped cream. Yield: 1 serving.

title: cheesed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli
in
small amount of boiling salted water until tender;
drain.
Combine
remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve over broccoli.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix all together except potato chips; top with potato chips and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
This makes a large sized Pyrex baking dishful.

title: sweet italian sausage
directions: Cut deer and pork into 3/4-inch cubes. Place in bowl. Mix all ingredients, except soy and Worcestershire sauce. Toss to coat. Now put soy and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and put in refrigerator for 8 hours. Next grind meat. Put into patties and fry. Good on pizzas or can freeze.

title: baked scallop casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion in butter.
Add scallops (washed and cut in half if they are large).
Cook a few minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine 1 can condensed Cheddar cheese soup with milk, lemon juice, pepper, marjoram and sherry.
Pour over scallops.
Top with bread crumbs and dabs of butter.

title: skillet baked beans
directions: In an iron skillet, brown onion and hamburger. Drain grease off and add rest of ingredients. Stir carefully and put bacon strips on top. Put skillet in oven. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Cover cukes with cold water; add 1 teaspoon soda.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Cover with cold water.
Add 2 teaspoons alum; boil 10 minutes.
Bring syrup of remaining ingredients to a boil; pour over fruit.
Let stand overnight.
The third day, repeat again.
The fourth day, reheat syrup and cukes together and seal in hot jars.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet; stir in seasonings. Blend well. Add Chex and pretzels and nuts. Mix until all pieces are coated. Cover skillet, leaving lid vents open. Heat at 250° for 15 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes. Cool on absorbent paper. Makes 9 cups.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and cook in salted water for 5 minutes.
Grease casserole dish; layer cabbage, diluted soup, crackers and cheese. Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Cook beans as directed on package.
Add drained water chestnuts and heat thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: brisket with onion gravy and vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring 2 cups water and the soup mix to boil in a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Remove from heat.
Scatter half the onions over soup mixture.
Add meat, fat side up. Scatter remaining onions on and around meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Put potatoes and carrots around meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours longer until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove meat to cutting board and slice across the grain in thin slices.
Serve with the vegetables and pan gravy.

title: round steak casserole deluxe
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; salt and pepper and flour. Brown in oil on both sides.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with soup and water.
Place onion slices on top.
Cover dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry banana smootie
directions: Put in blender. Blend until smooth. Makes 2 servings.

title: fried shrimp deluxe
directions: Clean shrimp, rinse and pat dry.
Combine crumbs, soup mix, parsley and cheese.
Dip shrimp into egg, drain well.
Coat shrimp lightly with crumbs.
Melt shortening in a large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Fry shrimp in a single layer for 3 minutes per side or until brown.

title: easy easter cheese
directions: Bring milk to a boil. In separate bowl, beat eggs with the sugar, salt and vanilla. Stir mixture into boiling milk. Continue stirring. When mixture looks like scrambled eggs and separates the water, remove from heat and pour into cheesecloth bag and make into a ball. Squeeze until the ball is firm and no water comes out. Drain about 1 hour. Remove cheesecloth and refrigerate. Slice.

title: crock-pot venison stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Pour water in to cover food.
Cook on high all day.

title: sausage and potato casserole(cachelada leonesa)
directions: Combine the following ingredients in pot: potatoes, sausage, salt and water.
Cover and cook gently for about 25 minutes.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk-egg mixture.
Add oil.
Drop into boiling liquid by teaspoon. Cook 5 minutes, uncovered, and 5 minutes longer, covered.
Keep small.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan and keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cheese, bacon and chilies.
Mix. Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Cut in squares, like fudge.
Good rewarmed in microwave for breakfast or snacks.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Combine the melted margarine with cracker crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: sinful blue cheese biscuits
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Place biscuits in melted butter, top with Blue cheese.
Bake at 375° until brown (approximately 15 minutes).

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, salt and baking powder (sifted together) alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.

title: mexican buffet
directions: Simmer ingredients for 2 to 3 hours.
Set up in containers for buffet.
Layer on your plate in this order:

title: bread
directions: Mix warm water, yeast, salt, lard and sugar.
Add warm milk and flour.

title: wild rice and shrimp
directions: Mix and put in a greased casserole.
Can be made up and put in refrigerator before baking.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: easy shrimp jambalaya
directions: Judge amounts of ingredients dependent upon amount of shrimp and how many people you plan to serve.

title: 5-minute choc-peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, marshmallows, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add milk chocolate chips, vanilla and peanut butter. Stir well and pour into a greased pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Use cake mix as directed.
Pour 1/4 cup of cake batter into flat-bottomed ice cream cones.
Place cones in oblong or square pan and cook like cupcakes.
Cool and ice.

title: 2 pounds macaroni and ham salad
directions: Cook macaroni until almost tender.
Rinse under cold water and drain.
Add Italian dressing and green onions.
Toss lightly. Cover; refrigerate for several hours.
In a very large bowl, combine macaroni mixture, ham, eggs, celery, green pepper, pimento and seasonings.
Add mayonnaise and blend.
Transfer to a clean glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: south of the border
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Cook rice until tender. Combine all ingredients and dice Velveeta into cubed for easy melting.
Simmer mixture until all cheese is melted and ready to serve.
Spoon mixture over Tostitos or tortilla chips.

title: wash day cobbler
directions: Pour fruit into ungreased cake pan.
Pour cake mix over fruit. Cut stick of butter into pats; place on cake mix, then sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients except boiling water; store in tightly covered container at room temperature up to 1 week.
Pour boiling water over tea mixture; stir until dissolved.
Garnish with lemon or
orange slices, if desired.
Makes 16 servings (about 3/4 cup each); contains 35 calories per serving.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream good first 5 ingredients and add flour and salt.
Stir into butter mixture the pecans.
Roll into small balls (will be dry).
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: apple oatmeal cookies(dietetic)
directions: Boil together water, apple and raisins for 3 minutes.
Drain well and squeeze out excess water.
Place raisins and apple in mixing bowl.
Add shortening and apple juice.
Cool.
Add eggs to this mixture.
Sift together the flour, salt and spices.
Combine flour mixture, oatmeal and nuts with the apple/raisin mixture. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
20 servings of 2 cookies each.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in small saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool, then pour into jar and refrigerate.
To serve, stir 2 tablespoons of syrup into 3/4 cup water.
Add ice.
Makes enough for 20 servings.

title: mock heath bar
directions: Spray a 10 x 15-inch pan (cookie sheet) with Pam.
Line pan with saltine crackers.
Take butter (not margarine) with sugar. Cook in saucepan until bubbly.
Pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When you remove from oven, take chocolate chips and spread as they melt.
Let cool and break apart. Delicious!

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve both jello in boiling water.
Set in freezer to just cool real well.
Remove from freezer and add pineapple and juice. Mix in another bowl the remaining ingredients.
Blend the 2 mixtures together and chill in refrigerator.
Salad is ready to slice and serve on lettuce leaf or by itself.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken until thin; dip in milk, then flour.
Melt margarine and olive oil.
Add crushed garlic.
Saute until garlic is fragrant.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Cook until done.
May add more wine, if needed to make sauce.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons water mixed with cornstarch (1 teaspoon).
Add chopped scallions during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Serve with hot fettucine noodles.
Serves 6.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix crabmeat, cheeses and onions in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt bea's egg custard
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until light and creamy.
Beat whites stiff.
Heat milk until tepid.
Pour over yolks and mix.
Fold together with egg whites.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until firm.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices. Chill. Garnish with drained pineapple chunks, if desired. Serve mixed with ginger ale, if you like it bubbly.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line 24 cupcake pans with cupcake liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill liners 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top each with a spoonful of filling and a teaspoon of nuts (optional).
Chill.
Serves 24.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish.
Add rice.
Add onion soup mix on top of rice.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour over all.
Cover with tin foil and bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place 1/2 cup chocolate morsels in top of a double boiler. Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cook until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally. Set aside to cool.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Stir in sugar and add butter. Stir in flour, cocoa and pecans. Add vanilla to mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Spread marshmallows over brownies while hot until melted.

title: lillian's easy, fast custard pie
directions: Heat milk.
Beat eggs well.
Add heated milk slowly to beaten eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: frisky puppies
directions: Melt sugar and ketchup and rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer.
Fry hot dogs or kielbasa in butter and simmer until brown.
You can double this recipe.

title: saucy fish sticks
directions: Place fish in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix together soup and milk.
Pour over fish.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until sauce is hot and bubbly.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: clam diggers(serves 8)
directions: Saute green pepper in butter in saucepan until tender.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Spoon into clam shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Mix ham, cheese and onions together until smooth. Spread 1/4 cup ham mixture on each tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edges. Roll up tortillas, starting from one edge. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours before serving.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef (sliced) on bottom of greased crock-pot. Wrap each piece of cut up chicken breast with strip of bacon and place on top of beef slices.
Layer with any pieces of beef left over.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add soup and tuna with 1/2 cup cheese. Place in casserole dish and spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Wash and cut the scallops to equal sizes.
Melt the butter and stir in the crumbs.
In a buttered baking dish (I prefer a glass casserole) put a layer of crumbs, half the scallops and half the cream, repeat with remainder of ingredients.
Salt and pepper each layer and cover with butter crumbs.
Sprinkle a little paprika on top.
Bake in 350° oven until crumbs are brown about 25 minutes.
I used to incorporate a couple of ounces of dry vermouth in the mixture.
Really enhances the flavor.
Never cook the scallops in aluminum dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cafe bavarian mint
directions: Mix ahead and store in airtight jars.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute finely chopped onions in margarine.
Add water, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.

title: rice pie
directions: Cover rice with water.
Add salt and shortening.
Simmer very slowly.
When dry, add cold milk a little at a time, until cooked. Let cool.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and Ricotta together and add to rice mixture.
Add pineapple.
Use your favorite crust or none at all.
Makes 2 (10-inch) pies or 1 (15 x 10-inch) Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water with salt until done.
Drain and save water. Saute onion in oil.
In blender, place potatoes, water, onion and parsley; blend until smooth.
Place mixture in pot, add milk. Stirring continuously, add cheese, butter and seasonings.
Heat until cheese is melted.
DO NOT BOIL.
Garnish with crumbled bacon when serving.
Thin with additional stock if necessary and adjust seasonings.
Heat slowly after adding the cheese or it will curdle.

title: italian slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion in bowl and top with sugar.
Bring to a boil vinegar, oil, salt, dry mustard, celery seed and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Cover and let stand 4 to 6 hours, then drain off all juice.
Mix and serve. Store in refrigerator.
Slaw is better after 2 or 3 days. Will keep up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, line bottom with whole graham crackers.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and remainder of mixture; another layer of graham crackers.
Top with chocolate icing.
Chill overnight.

title: never hard frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk to thick paste, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix sugar, salt, vanilla and shortening to creamy state.
Add to flour and milk.
Cream all together on high speed. Refrigerates and freezes well for future use.

title: brownie bites
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, water and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cocoa powder and baking powder until well mixed.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spray the bottom only of an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly.
Remove from pan.
Cut into 8 bars. Sprinkle with the powdered sugar.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; stir well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: all-purpose crepe batter 1
directions: Whisk Method:
Combine eggs and salt.
Gradually add flour with milk, beating with electric mixer or whisk until smooth.
Beat in butter.

title: date bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in nuts and dates.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread cherry pie filling in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Spread pineapple on top of filling. Sprinkle with sugar.
Smooth dry cake mix on top of fruit layers. Pour margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Good served with vanilla ice cream.

title: delicious hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Let set in bowl until soft.
Mix remaining sugar and Crisco until fluffy. Add egg; mix well.
Then add flour, salt, lukewarm water and milk gradually until it makes a soft dough.
You can refrigerate the dough until it rises double or set in a warm place free from drafts until double.

title: cranberry-glazed ham
directions: Place ham, fat side up, on rack in shallow pan.
Score fat in diamond pattern; stud with whole cloves.
Insert meat thermometer. Bake ham in 325° oven until meat thermometer registers 140°, about 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: candy covered peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large iron skillet and cook until all water evaporates.
Pour into shallow pan and bake at 300° until peanuts are done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the cheeses and melt in crock-pot.
Brown ground beef and onion and add to cheese.
Chop green peppers and tomatoes and add to rest of mixture.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Will thicken as it cooks, or add a little flour to thicken.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed.
Stuff each mushroom with a spoonful of filling. Brush with butter and broil.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: surprise corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients. Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 8 or more.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
May add pimentos, green onion tops, jalapenos or long green peppers to taste.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on box.
Cut cheese in cubes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beef stroganoff ala hershey
directions: Shake beef cubes in sack with flour until all are evenly floured.
Brown cubed meat in butter or melted beef fat.
When all sides are lightly browned, add sliced onion and garlic clove. Continue to brown, stirring to keep from sticking.
When onion is transparent, add beef broth.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender to fork.
Salt and pepper to taste before broth is added.
Fold in sour cream and reheat, but do not allow to boil.
Then noodles may be added to the hot meat mixture and allowed to stand, uncovered, until cool.

title: party punch
directions: In punch bowl, pour in the club soda and frozen orange juice. Stir until melted.
Add sugar and vodka.
Then spoon in lemon sherbet and allow to float on top.
Be sure to stir as serving.

title: calzone
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Line bottom with 1 package crescent rolls, pinching seams. Layer as follows: Provolone, salami, pepperoni, peppers, mushrooms, ham and Swiss. Cover with second package crescent rolls, pinching seams.

title: graham mac nut treat
directions: Boil butter and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add Macadamia nuts. Line cookie sheet with foil.
Spread nut syrup on crackers, place on foil, bake at 325° for 15 minutes or less.
Take off pan immediately.

title: easy rolls or bread(pizza dough)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and salt.
Mix well, adding flour last.
Let rise in a warm place, covered.
Form into desired shapes in greased cupcake pans or in pie plates.
Let rise again, about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This dough may be used to make pizza shells or make 2 large cookie sheets for square pizzas.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, squash and vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to eggs and squash mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a loaf pan or tube pan which has been greased and floured.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Gradually blend mayonnaise into cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add strawberries 1/4 cup at a time so that mixture will not curdle. Add lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 8-inch pan. Freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in a large heavy saucepan until crisp.
Remove bacon and add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been mashed or cut into small pieces.
Stir in navy beans along with salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add crumbled bacon and parsley flakes.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve in warm soup bowls.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water, lemon juice and salt.
Let set until Jell-O starts congealing, then add the pineapple, carrots and pecans.

title: cool dip chicken wings
directions: Break chicken wings into drumettes and discard wing tips.
Dip chicken into milk and roll in dry Ranch mix.
Pour extra mix over pieces.
Put on cookie tray and bake 15 to 20 minutes until done at 350°.
Serve with celery sticks and Ranch dressing.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix it all together. Chill in refrigerator overnight or chill in freezer 1 hour.
Roll out and cut them out. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: garlic slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in thin slices. (Do not chop or grate.) Combine cabbage, water, vinegar, oil and minced garlic. Let set 3 days, stirring once each day.

title: pennsylvania cocoa cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until mixture is fluffy after each addition.
Make a paste of the cocoa and coffee.
Dissolve soda in warm water. Add the cocoa mixture to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and soda mixture.
Stir to form a smooth batter.
Bake in greased oblong pan (about 13 x 9-inch) at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: mamaw miracle's gravy
directions: Take biscuits and add water; beat until a liquid.
Put into a pint jar and add water until full.
Shake well.
Pour into a skillet; bring to a boil and stir until thickened.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in butter or margarine until cooked. Puree in blender.
Add juice, broth, curry, chives, salt and pepper.
Heat and serve.

title: creamy cheesey potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes. Put in oblong casserole.
Dot with 1 stick of butter.
Stir in salt, pepper and onion.
In a bowl, blend sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Spread mixture over potatoes. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese, then cornflakes.
Dot with 1/2 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake mix package in 9 x 13-inch pan. Poke holes in cake.
Mix pina colada and Eagle Brand milk and pour over cake.
Let cool.
Spread can of pineapple over cake, then spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top (optional).

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Whip confectioners sugar, Cool whip and cream cheese; spread over cooled crust.
Cook pudding and milk until thick.
Cool.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut.

title: beth's poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except poppy seed) together and mix for a while until light and smooth. Add poppy seed.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes.
Should not be too firm or liquidy.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream together.
Cover large pizza pan or cookie sheet with foil.
Spread cream cheese mixture on pan.
Spread taco sauce over mixture.
Chop onions, peppers and tomatoes into small pieces.
Put on top of mixture.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange slice-pecan bars
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl. Add shortening and sugar. Mix flour, pecans and orange slices and blend into eggs. Add vanilla and salt. Spread batter onto greased 13 x 17 jelly roll baking pan and bake for 40 minutes at 325°. Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars and sprinkle with finely chopped pecans. Remove from pan while warm.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs well together.
Put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the water over the pebbles in a quiet stream. Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun. When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: cheese olive appetizers
directions: Drain olives on paper towels.
Mix other 4 ingredients well. Cover each olive.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen until serving time.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, syrup
and	sugar.	Bring
to
boil and let boil 6 minutes,
stirring	constantly.
Take
off heat and add other ingredients, stirring until foamy and pour on corn.
Put in pan and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Can be stored in freezer.

title: creamed cabbage or cucumbers
directions: Mix together.
Pour over cabbage or cucumbers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, coconut, cocoa and vanilla in a bowl; set aside. Boil butter, milk and sugar for 2 minutes. Pour over oatmeal mixture. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
