directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Pour coconut and pecans in pan. Mix the cake mix by package directions, then pour over coconut and pecans in pan. Mix together the cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and 10x sugar. Pour over cake mix and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: frosty ice cream
directions: Mix canned milk and Cool Whip with mixer.
Add about 1/2 gallon of chocolate milk and the syrup.
Mix well and pour into ice cream maker.
Use remaining chocolate milk, if needed, to fill up the rest of the ice cream maker.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Drop cabbage leaves into salted boiling water and parboil 5 minutes. Drain. Combine ground beef, rice, parsley, egg, milk, 1/2 of onion, salt and pepper. Place a large spoonful on each leaf. Roll up and fasten with toothpick. Melt shortening in skillet, brown cabbage rolls evenly. Sprinkle with brown sugar, cover with soup and water. Add remaining onion, bay leaf and cloves. Cover and simmer 1 hour, 15 minutes. Serves: 12.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla (by hand) until thoroughly mixed.
Pinch off and roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Stick toothpicks into peanut butter balls.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and place on wax paper to set.
Remove from wax paper and store in covered containers in cool dry place.

title: reece's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix and pat into bacon or deli keeper.
Melt 12 ounce package chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in small amount of cooking oil.
Add peppers, soups, Ragu sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook until well blended, about 10 minutes.
Place layers or tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of meat mixture.
Alternate layers.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir into banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts; mix well.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets whole, then skin under cold water.
Slice or dice beets.
Put sugar, water and vinegar in large pan and bring to boil.
Put spices in cloth bag and add.
Boil 10 minutes; add cut beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in hot sterile jars.
No processing needed.

title: chocolate ice box delight
directions: Combine flour and butter, mix in pecans.
Put in a 13 x 9 inch baking Pyrex and press to form crust, bottom only.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes, or until light brown. Cool. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread this over the crust, very carefully.
Add more Cool Whip if needed.
Combine both pudding mixes and milk according to the directions on the package.
Spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on the top. It can be topped with a shredded Hershey bar and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.

title: chicken in a pan
directions: Roll your chicken inside of crescent rolls.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix broth, soup and vegetables.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 400° until rolls are browned.

title: auntie's chocolate cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool.
Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Blend in milk until smooth.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Press plastic wrap on surface.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: elaine's easy key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and lime juice in large bowl.
Carefully fold in cool whip.
Pour mixture into pie crusts; freeze pies until ready to serve.

title: choco-mint meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and vinegar for 10 minutes and gradually add sugar.
Mixture should get stiff and form soft peaks.
Add mint flavoring and a few drops of green food coloring to get a light green color.
Stir in the chocolate morsels.
Drop from a teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet (easier if the cookie sheets are covered with aluminum foil).
Put in oven and turn off heat.
Leave for 4 hours.
Makes 85 to 100 cookies.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl; set aside.
Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla for 1 minute.
Add flour mixture.
Stir with spoon to blend.
Add apples and nuts.
Do not overmix.
Split batter into 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes before removing from pan.

title: texas hot mixture
directions: Brown together ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain.
Add the other ingredients and serve on hot dogs in buns with chopped onions, mixed with a teaspoon of vinegar and mustard.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries into graham cracker crust.
Boil Jell-O, sugar, water and cornstarch together for 3 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Then pour over berries in crust.
Chill in refrigerator. When cool, put Cool Whip on top.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place mayonnaise in 1-quart jar.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours for flavors to blend.
To serve, mix equal parts of dressing and sour cream.
Add milk only if you prefer thinner dressing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Cool chicken; debone and shred meat.
In a large bowl, mix the sour cream, chiles, soup, onion and 1/2 of the cheese.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the mixture for topping.
Add shredded meat to the remainder of the mixture. Place meat mixture by spoonfuls into tortillas.
Roll up and place seam side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add broth to reserved sour cream mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over the enchiladas. Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Heat 2 cups of water to boiling.
Add Jell-O and sugar, stirring to dissolve.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices. Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet and pour in ginger ale.
Yields 6 1/2 quarts approximately.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto aluminum foil-lined greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Macaroons will stick if allowed to cool.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn and biscuit mix.
Add egg, oil and milk.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9-inch square casserole dish.
Cover with cheese; top with chilies.
Spread remaining corn mixture on top of this and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy drop rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add all other ingredients and stir until blended
(dough will be soft and sticky).
Place in airtight,
covered container and store in refrigerator several hours before
using.
To serve, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
The entire recipe will yield 3 dozen rolls
or
dozen
small
ones, and the ones made in small muffin tins are especially tasty.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Save 1/2 cup of cheese for the top.
Layer 1/2 of chilies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 cup of cheese.
Layer 1/2 of onion. Repeat layers.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add broth, onion, paste, kidney beans and garlic powder.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Then add 2 cups macaroni; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until pasta is tender.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: quick plum or apricot bread
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350° in two loaf pans.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Microwave cheese and chili in a bowl until cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup with chicken.
Add celery, pimento and sour cream. Put in greased casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick oleo with 1 1/2 cup coarse cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons poppy seed for topping. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chili con carne(weight watchers)
directions: Brown onions, meat and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer covered over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 2 hours.
Add drained beans; simmer uncovered until desired consistency.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets (not peeled).
Once they are cool enough to handle, pick off skins and cut into chunks, not thin, or salad becomes "mushy".
Place hot dressing mixture over potatoes while they are still warm, if possible; this is best.*

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook cubed, peeled eggplant and onions in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Mix with milk, eggs, 1/2 cup cheese and dressing in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Add remaining cheese to top and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Boil some water.
Put in carrots and turnips.
Cook until half done.
Remove and put in a bowl with cold water, then drain the vegetables.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Let partly congeal.
Add Cool Whip, cheese and pecans.
Pour into Pyrex dish (8 x 10-inch) and let congeal.
Serves 12.
Use mold.
Makes a pretty dessert.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in greased casserole dish. Set in a pan of water and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool some.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin; mix well.
Fold whipped cream into gelatin.
Pour into crust made of 1/2 pound graham crackers and 1/3 cup of melted butter.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and let sit for 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pudding will thicken as it cools.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Gently fold powdered custard mix into defrosted Cool Whip. When completely blended, add rum to taste.
Fold gently again. Chill overnight for best taste and consistency.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a saucepan over low heat. Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add last 4 ingredients to the pan.
Stir one to two minutes until it is all melted.
Pour into 9-inch pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar with eggs. Add salt, flour and baking soda. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and fruit cocktail. Beat until fruit cocktail is in small pieces. Put batter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together brown sugar, nuts and coconut. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and sugar with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread into crust.
Layer strawberries on top of cream cheese; leave some to garnish.

title: green stuff(salad or dessert)
directions: Combine all ingredients and it's ready to eat.
Put nuts on top for salad or Cool Whip, nuts and cherries for dessert.
Keeps well.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 8-inch square baking pan. Melt cheese and half the butter in pan until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Pour over broccoli.
Toss crackers with remaining butter in bowl. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: s'more gorp
directions: In a medium paper bag or large plastic bag, combine all of the ingredients. Close bag and shake well. Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir together and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil until golden brown.

title: hawaiian style chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken; set aside.
Saute diced bell pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add salt, pepper and olive oil.
Pull apart chicken and add to mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes (you may add chicken broth for additional moisture).
In separate boiler, cook rice according to directions (you may substitute chicken broth for water).
When done, place in serving dish and put chicken mixture over rice.

title: no egg vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well. Pour into freezer can of 5 quart freezer. Process according to freezer directions.

title: speedy orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour, butter, sugar, salt and egg.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (about 2 minutes). Cover; let rest 15 minutes.
Roll dough to a 14 x 7-inch rectangle; spread with half of Orange Filling, leaving a 1-inch margin on long sides.
Roll dough, jellyroll fashion, starting at long side.
Pinch seam to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut into 12 equal slices; place slices, cut side down, in greased muffin pans. Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 30 minutes.
Bake rolls at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread remaining Orange Filling over tops of rolls.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: beer muffins
directions: Pour beer into large bowl.
Add sugar and beer until sugar dissolves (it will be foamy).
Add biscuit mix and stir just until mix is moistened well.
Grease muffin tins.
Allow a heaping tablespoon of batter for each muffin.
Let rise 20 minutes.

title: wagon wheel pie
directions: Steam onions in margarine in covered pan over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cut Spam lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside 5 slices.
Cut remaining slices into bite size pieces.
Combine Spam pieces, vegetables, onions and all remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cut reserved Spam slices in half diagonally; arrange on filling.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°. Cool 10 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Grate rind from clean lemon.
Juice the
lemon;
add to grated rind
and set aside.
Preheat oven to 325° (glass pan) or
350° (metal
pan).
Blend sugar, egg yolks, margarine and salt thoroughly.
Add
lemon juice and rind and flour;
blend well. Gradually stir in milk.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks. Fold
in egg whites to lemon-milk mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie
crust and bake 1 hour.
Insert table knife;
blade comes out
clean
if done.
Cake
comes
to
top,
lemon custard on bottom.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Mix beef, small onion, rice and salt and pepper.
Stuff peppers and place in saucepot. Mix tomato sauce and water.
Pour over peppers.
Top with sliced onion and celery leaves.
Cook 45 minutes over medium heat.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Split chicken breasts and remove skin and bone, if desired. Arrange in shallow 2 or 3 quart baking dish.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir together soup and wine; spoon evenly over chicken.
Coarsely crush stuffing mix and sprinkle over top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50-55 minutes or until chicken is tender.
8 servings.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer at least 2 hours or longer (covered).

title: hawaiian delight salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package; let set until livery thick. With mixer, add Cool Whip until well blended.
Fold in fruit. Pour into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Set until firm.
Garnish with cherry halves.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Line pie pan with pie crust.
Set aside.
Brown bacon, drain and dice.
Cool.
Combine eggs, cheese and onion salt in medium bowl.
Stir in bacon.
Add cream or milk and blend well.
Pour egg mixture into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until center is clean.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top before putting in oven.

title: stuffed breast of veal
directions: Saute onion and celery in chicken fat until brown.
Add matzo meal, salt, pepper, hot water and beaten eggs.
Fill veal pocket with mixture.
Sew opening with white thread.
Place in basting pan.
Add tomato sauce can of water.
Sprinkle with paprika and garlic powder.
Cover and roast at 350° for about 3 hours or until tender.
Uncover during last half of baking to brown meat.
Baste frequently.

title: pecan logs
directions: Beat milk and sugar until smooth. Knead and shape into 4 logs, each about 5-inches long. Place on wax paper. Melt caramels, butter and water in top of boiler. Pour onto logs a little at a time. Roll in 1 1/2 cups pecans, chopped.

title: barbecued beef on buns
directions: Place beef, onion and celery in Dutch oven.
Add water to almost cover meat.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat; strain and reserve cooking liquid.
Trim and shred meat; return to Dutch oven.
Add 2 cups of the strained cooking liquid (save remaining cooking liquid) and chill.
Skim and discard fat.
Add all seasonings; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add additional reserved liquid if necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until the meat falls off the bones.
Tear chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken in buttered pan.
Mix soups and sour cream together, then pour over chicken.
Pour crushed crackers over mixture.
Sprinkle seed.
Pour butter or margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Slice 1 1/2 of the bananas.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Pour pudding over banana slices.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Spread whipped topping over pie.
Garnish with remaining banana, sliced and dipped in lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Store leftover pie in the refrigerator.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Mix and set at room temperature covered at least 2 hours; better if it sets several hours.
Cook 1 pound spaghetti.
Drain spaghetti.
While still hot, toss with sauce.
Once tossed, sit 5 minutes to allow cheese to melt.
Toss again, then serve.

title: mrs. brandt's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening and add sugars, blending until light.
Beat in egg yolks to which the cold water has been added.
Add vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and add gradually, beating after each addition.
Pat the dough into a 17 x 11-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 cup brown sugar gradually and beat until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Stir in chocolate chips and spread topping over the dough.
Bake 30 minutes.
Allow to stand 1 hour before cutting into squares.

title: old-fashioned apple butter cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy and light.
Add eggs and beat until blended. Add apple butter and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients slowly, alternately with sour cream.
Mix until well blended.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into a greased, floured loaf pan.
Mix together:
1/2 C. sugar, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg, 1 tsp. cinnamon and 1/2 C. chopped walnuts.
Sprinkle half this topping over mixture, then pour remaining batter over top and sprinkle rest of topping on top layer.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or topping.

title: hot sausages
directions: Dissolve grape jelly and mustard and keep heated in a fondue pot.
Add sausages just before serving.
May use a regular pot and place in a bowl before serving.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead until well mixed.
Cover and let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Knead again and roll into crust shapes (makes 3 to 4 crusts). Top with desired toppings. Bake at 425° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg yolk.
Mix well; add bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream while adding to sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla, stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.
Turn into an 8 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When cool, cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into regular graham cracker crust or chocolate cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: jon ben getty
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Drain and add the rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer until everything is hot.
Add slices of American cheese on top and simmer until cheese is melted.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator or drop from a teaspoon right away.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or less; do not overbake.
Good with cream cheese frosting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook in boiling water (with small amount of oil from dressing) until tender.
Run under cold water and drain.

title: most excellent cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs, honey and vanilla. Combine flour, coarse oatmeal, salt, baking powder
and soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in grated candy, nuts and chocolate chips.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Roll into 1 1/2-inch diameter balls. Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp salad hilary
directions: Prepare shrimp.

In a large pot, bring 6 quarts of water to a boil with 2 tablespoons of salt. When the water has reached a rolling boil, add all the shrimp at once. Cook, uncovered, until the shrimp are pink and tender, about 3 minutes. Drain the shrimp into a colander and rinse immediately under cold running water to prevent further cooking; drain well. Shell the shrimp and devein, if desired. Split them in half lengthwise and place in a large bowl.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces. Add to the shrimp.
Add the tomatoes and scallions.

title: crunchy ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Blend soup, sour cream and milk.
Mix macaroni and ham.
Pour half of soup mixture over macaroni.
Arrange broccoli on top.
Pour over rest of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: date cake
directions: Cut dates.
Sprinkle with soda.
Add boiling water.
Let cool. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and dates mixture.
Add flour, spices and salt which have been sifted 3 times.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese salad
directions: Grind together all cheeses, pimentos, eggs and onion.
Add vinegar and mix.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and sugar to desired taste.
Mix well.
Roll into ball.
Roll ball in crushed nuts or Ritz crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: double crust pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle cold water evenly over surface; stir with a fork until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball; chill.
Crust for double crust 9-inch pie.

title: appalachian apple pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except apples.
Add apples to mixture, tossing to coat fruit.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Rub leg of lamb thoroughly with a half of lemon.
Make a few holes here and there and stick in tiny slivers of garlic.
Dredge lightly with flour, sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and paprika and place in roaster, fat side up.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes to the pound, uncovered.
Serve with mint jelly or sauce.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix orange sauce ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat while stirring and cook until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Cool and chill.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover when begins to burn.
Bake for approximately 2 hours at 325° or 350°.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cocoa together.
Separate egg yolks and egg whites (reserved for top).
Mix 1 cup milk and 3 egg yolks together.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add rest of milk.
Cook on top of stove in a good heavy saucepan, stirring constantly so it won't stick or scorch.
When gets thick, remove from stove.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into 9 1/2-inch cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar gradually while beating for 1 minute longer. Spread on top of pie.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Mix rice and onion in a sauce pan, with oil.
Fry for 10 minutes.
Drained and mix with all other ingredients except cheese - put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degree for one hour with lid on.
Put cheese on top - bake for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peanutty pretzels
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.
May have to refrigerate candy to get it firm.

title: arkansas earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Prepare cake according to package directions and pour in pan. Beat until smooth cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo. Drop over top of batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sift together the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Cream the butter and add the sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until creamy.
Alternately, add sour cream and flour mixture to the batter, beating in between and ending with flour mixture.
Add almond extract.
You'll be splitting the batter into 3 layers for this cake, so use about 1/3 of the batter for each layer.
Put a layer of batter in bottom of Bundt pan.
Place 1/3 of the nuts and cranberry sauce on top.
Repeat 2 more times.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool cake for about 10 minutes and remove from Bundt pan, top side up.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet, saute margarine and onions.
When tender, add ground beef and fry.
Drain fat and add soup, mushrooms, garlic salt and pepper.
While simmering, prepare noodles.
Add cooked noodles to beef mixture.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together cheese, dressing, lemon juice and ketchup until smooth.
Fold in onion and shrimp.

title: blueberry clafouti
directions: Coat 2 (10 ounce) custard cups with cooking spray.
Place 1/2 cup blueberries into each cup; set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and next 6 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Pour mixture evenly over blueberries.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mash potatoes until fluffy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown. Makes 3 pies.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir beef and onion until light brown; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate; top with green chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer, if needed.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries into pie shell. Cook on stove top, sugar, cornstarch, jello and water until thick. Pour mixture over strawberries into pie shell. Chill overnight. Pie may be topped with whip cream if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, spaghetti mix and onion together.
Then add the other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes. Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spoon approximately 1/4 cup batter in each cone.
Set cones on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon frosting over cakes and garnish with sprinkles.

title: peanut-honey cookies
directions: On sheet of wax paper or a paper plate, sift together flour and baking soda; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: butter crunch
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart pan over low heat.
Remove.
Add sugar until blended.
Return to low heat.
Stir rapidly until thoroughly mixed and begins to bubble.
Add water and corn syrup. Stir frequently; cook until thermometer reads 290°, brittle, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat at once.
Sprinkle in nuts, quickly mix.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool at room temperature.
As crunch cools loosen from sheet with spatula, 2 to 3 times.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 350° for 30 minutes.
Beat until stiff peaks.
Scoop onto baked
pie and bake until meringue is light brown.
Cool and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix spices, except nutmeg, with salt, sugar and flour. Add to pumpkin. Add milk and beaten eggs. Pour in pie pans. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 50 minutes. Pie will test done when clean knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Flour and grease 1 large pie pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Chop vegetables and
rinse.
Steam in water that clings to vegetables until tender.
Add tomato juice and simmer until ready to serve.
Even better the next day.

title: deedee's cinnamon apple dump cake
directions: Place ingredients in 9 x 13 pan in this order:
pie filling, half the dry cake mix, cinnamon, pecans and remaining cake mix. Drizzle evenly with margarine or cover the top with margarine slices.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes at 450 degrees.
Lower heat to 350 and bake 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Grate 2 cups of zucchini with 2 1/2 medium onions onto wax paper.
Beat eggs, ad to Bisquick mix and Parmesan cheese.
Mix with zucchini and onions.
Fry into pancake rounds.
Like potato patties.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, evaporated milk (less 2 tablespoons), butter and nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into 9 x 12-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels and 2 tablespoons reserved evaporated milk.
Pour over baked cake mixture.
Pour chocolate chips over caramels.
Press remaining 1/2 cake mixture over chocolate chips by using your hands.
It is very hard to make this cover the chips entirely, but do your best. Bake at 350° for 20 more minutes.

title: vegie-meat cups
directions: Combine all the ingredients (except the mashed potatoes) into 4 patties.
Shape over upside-down custard cups.
Chill up to 1 hour. Place inverted cups in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 6 to 8-cup casserole. With a sharp knife, split each row of corn kernels on each ear of corn down the center. Scrape enough kernels off the cobs to measure 2 1/2 cups.
Beat the egg, light cream, heavy cream and brown sugar in a mixing bowl just until blended.
Stir in the chives and nutmeg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir in the corn.
Toss 1/2 cup cracker crumbs with 3 tablespoons of the melted butter in a large mixing bowl, then stir in the corn mixture.
Pour the corn mixture into the prepared casserole.
Toss the remaining 3 tablespoons cracker crumbs with remaining 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle the crumbs over the top of the pudding.
Bake the pudding, uncovered, until light golden brown and slightly firm to the touch, 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: clam fettucini
directions: Cook noodles according to package, then drain. Return to pan and add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly. Turn off heat. Cover and let sit until liquid is absorbed or if you prefer more moisture, serve immediately.
This recipe is easy, low-fat and delicious!

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In a skillet saute ground chuck and onions until brown.
Drain.
Add Prego and mushrooms.
Remove from heat.

title: rice savory salad
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Mix rice with onions, celery, pepper, peas, broccoli and mushrooms.
Combine oil, soy sauce, balsamic vinegar and curry powder.
Add to rice mixture.
Stir gently. Refrigerate 24 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times.
At serving time, gently mix in noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cover, then take off cover, stir and bake 15 minutes longer.
(Only stir 1 time.)

title: crunch salad
directions: Dice into small pieces all ingredients.
At serving time, cover with Caesar dressing.
Serve in bowl or pita pockets.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Grate the washed, unpeeled zucchini onto a clean kitchen towel. Wring out excess water.
Put in a bowl with enough Bisquick and beer to make a fairly firm batter.
Salt and pepper to taste. Amounts depend on the size of the zucchini.
Fry in 1 inch of hot oil until brown.
Serve hot.

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add 1/2 the onion and picante sauce.
Sprinkle a small amount of cheese in meat.
Roll in tortillas.
Top with cheese, lettuce, tomato, onion and picante sauce.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 10 inch bundt pan; set aside. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour in pan. Bake for 1 hr.

title: crab casserole a la rudy
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in sour cream and blend well.
Pour into preheated skillet and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then cut and serve.

title: perfect divinity
directions: In
2-quart
saucepan,
combine
cups sugar, 1/2 cup light corn
syrup,
cup hot water and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boil. Cook
to hard ball stage (250°) without stirring.
Wipe crystals
from sides of pan now and then with fork wrapped in damp cloth.
Remove from heat.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend together and put in jar and leave in refrigerator for about 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, sour cream and soup.
Add chicken, chopped up with broccoli, and 4 ounces of cheese.
Mix together with salt and pepper, if desired.
Pour into a casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with Durkee onions.
Bake at 400° until it bubbles.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch) with nacho chips.
Mix cooked ground beef, refried beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning together over heat. Pour mixture over chips and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When casserole is done, add shredded lettuce, chopped onion, chopped bell pepper, 1/2 avocado, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese over it.
Serve with sour cream and picante sauce.

title: taco burgers
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, milk, taco seasoning mix and onion together in a large bowl.
Form into patties.
Fry patties over medium heat until done.
Drain all fat from patties.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to good boil. Take off burner and mix in peanut butter. Mix well, then add cornflakes, stirring until coated. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: banana split
directions: Crush graham crackers and add 1/4 cup of oleo; mix well.
Pat down in 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and oleo with mixer for 10 minutes.
Put on top of graham crackers. Slice bananas and put pineapple on top.
Then whip Dream Whip as directed.
Pour on top of fruit.
Top with ground walnuts.

title: grape pie
directions: Remove skins from grapes.
Put pulp in a pan without water and bring to a boil.
While hot, put through sieve to remove seeds. Now, combine skins and pulp with the rest of the ingredients. Pour into pie shell and bake.
(I always put a crust on top.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Mix in mayonnaise, eggs, mushroom soup and onion.
Set aside.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over stuffing.
Mix.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in a baking dish.
Pour broccoli mixture on top and then place a layer of Cheddar cheese on top.
Top all of this with the remaining crumb mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered mango dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cut in butter.
Press evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill until firm.
Soften gelatin in water.
Add boiling water and the remaining 1 cup of sugar.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in lemon juice and mangoes.
Carefully spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.
Cut into serving pieces.
Makes 24.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs and sugar.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Beat in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 55 minutes until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Top with pie filling. Refrigerate leftover cake.

title: egg breakfast casserole
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with bread cubes.
Pour melted margarine over cubes.
Beat milk, salt, mustard and eggs until fluffy.
Add cheese, meat and mushrooms.
Pour over bread. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove and let set for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple mandarin chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in single layer in baking dish that has been sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray.
Spread orange sections and pineapple evenly over chicken.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: hot corn
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter together.
Add corn and jalapeno pepper.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandmother quinn's christmas cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add vanilla, eggs and milk.
Mix.
Then add 7+ cups sifted flour.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll thin and cut cookies.
Bake about 10 minutes at 325° on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Makes approximately 95 Christmas figure cookies.

title: scones
directions: Mix together.
Drop by tablespoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Brush top with egg white, sprinkle top with sugar.
Put back in oven and bake 3 minutes more.
Makes about 9 scones.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients together.

title: zucchini bread or cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Then add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla and beat well.
Then add flour, salt, cinnamon and pineapple for cake.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° in loaf pan.
Best served warm.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 24 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef. Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender. Drain. Return to the skillet and add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Mix well.
Drain beans and add to meat mixture.
Put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Add bacon strips and cook 15 minutes. (Or cook in crock-pot on low 5 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking.)

title: scalloped pork and potato casserole
directions: Combine all but cheese.
Put in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add cheese to top. Return to oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Check potatoes for doneness.

title: grandma smith's chiliburgers
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Combine rest of ingredients.
Add to meat mixture. Simmer 15 minutes. Enjoy!

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten eggs, then add flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Wet hands in cold water and press in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Leave excess water on bread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and eggs.
Set aside. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased generously and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes. When cool, sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies, our way
directions: You will need one 1 1/2 to 4 year old child (boy or girl).
I chose my son, Devin.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, barely cover potatoes and onion with water and boil until tender.
Add milk, margarine and seasonings; heat on medium temperature until bubbly (do not boil).
Heat for about 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: prune cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour; place on bottom rack.

title: fat-free bread pudding
directions: *Use fat-free egg substitute.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° until brown.

title: honey apples
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine honey, salt, cinnamon and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Add apples.
Decrease heat and simmer until tender.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly. Bake at 425° for one hour or until done. Cool slightly or until safe to handle. Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise. Carefully scoop out pulp, being careful not to tear skins. Mash potato pulp until no lumps remain. Add milk a little at a time, mixing well until pulp is smooth. Add margarine, sour cream,
pepper and salt. Mix well. Stir in cheese and chives. Mix well. Spoon potato mixture into shells until full.** Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes. Garnish with chopped chives, if desired.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Do not remove the husk and silk from the corn.
Secure ends of husk with string.
Cook in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes or until the corn kernels are tender when pierced through the husk.
Remove from the oven and allow to stand for 3 minutes before removing husk and silk (be careful, corn is very hot).
Serve with butter, salt and pepper.

title: three-bean crock-pot beans
directions: Brown and drain (if necessary) the ground beef.
Cut bacon in half.
Put beef and bacon in crock-pot followed by all the other ingredients.
Mix and cook on low overnight or all day while at work.
Allow 7 to 8 hours!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon.
When almost done, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix Shake 'n Bake and Parmesan to taste together.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then dip into mixture.
Coat chicken well, then roll up and place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Take out of oven 5 minutes before done and cover with cheese slices.
Finish cooking.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Brush bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking oil.
Mix Parmesan cheese with Bisquick, Italian seasoning, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Arrange chicken, skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°; turn chicken.
Divide chili sauce over breasts. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Bake until melted.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover with topping, and bake at 375 degrees until golden brown.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place ingredients as listed in layers.
Let stand, covered, 12 hours or overnight.
Mix thoroughly before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat until cream. Add flour, salt, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Add water, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle fried bacon, cheese and onion in a pastry shell. Beat eggs, cream, salt, sugar and pepper; pour in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°; then reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake another 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: mint chocolate chip ice cream
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, extract and food coloring if desired; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer container. Freeze according to manufacturers instructions. Freeze leftovers.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour and butter.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 300° oven.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on top.
Mix pudding with milk; spread on top of cream cheese.
Spread a large container of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Put nuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use about a teaspoon of dough for each pie.
Roll out on floured board and fill with your favorite pie filling.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs, flour and buttermilk together.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Pour into pie shell; dust with nutmeg.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool; shape into balls and roll in flaked coconut.

title: krispie roll
directions: Cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture firmly into greased 15 x 10 x 3/4-inch jelly roll pan.
Remove Rice Krispies mixture from pan and put on countertop.
Melt remaining butter with milk over low heat.
Remove from heat and sift in icing sugar and cocoa.
Blend.
Spread cocoa mixture evenly on top of Krispie.
Starting at short end, roll up to form a log.
Wrap in greased wax paper and refrigerate until firm.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: sweet onion relish
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add onion quarters, a few at a time.
Process until finely chopped.
Combine 12 cups onion and salt in a large bowl.
Let stand 30 minutes. Drain squeezing all excess juice from mixture.
Place pickling spice on a 6-inch square of cheesecloth.
Tie with string. Combine onion, spice bag, sugar and remaining ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook about 30 minutes or until mixture is thick.
Remove and discard spice bag. Pack onion mixture into hot jars, filling to 1/2-inch from top. Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw on hands.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: amaretto fruit dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Serve over fruit salad fruit slices such as apples.

title: crisp and chunky meal-in-one salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce thoroughly.
Tear into bite-size pieces. Place in a large salad bowl.
Add grapes, turkey, cheeses, oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Toss lightly.

title: ground beef patties with cheese sauce
directions: Mix meat, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and eggs.
Divide into four parts; shape into patties.
Place into a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or done to your liking.

title: cinnamon spiced cucumber rings
directions: Wash, peel and remove seeds from enough yellow cucumbers for 1 gallon, sliced 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with lime mixed with 4 1/2 cups water in a pan and let set 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well. Soak rings in clear water for 3 hours.
Mix together 1/2 cup cider vinegar, red food coloring, alum and enough water to cover rings and simmer 2 hours.
Drain well.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt oleo, on low heat, with onions.
Add cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crab meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cook until it thickens.
Cool.
Whip 1/2 pt. whipping cream. Mix all together and spread on top of Jello.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix eggs, mustard, sugar, flour and salt well.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil, turn heat down to low and add egg mixture. Stir constantly until thick.
Cool.
Add salad dressing.
Excellent for potato salad or chicken salad.

title: barbecue oven tender chicken
directions: Heat oven to 300° to 350°.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 hour or until chicken is cooked through.

title: italian sirloin stew(in 30 minutes)
directions: Cut beef steak into 1/4-inch thick strips, then cut each strip into 1-inch pieces.
Combine garlic with 1 tablespoon oil; stir into beef and reserve.
Saute onion in remaining oil in large saucepan 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with basil and pepper; cook and stir 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, beef broth and zucchini.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: simple strawberry marshmallow dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk until smooth.
Great dip for all kinds of fruit.

title: microwaved glazed onions
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard, pepper, salt and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water, stirring until smooth.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring often.
Slice onions thinly and separate into rings.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Cut bread into little pieces.
Pour margarine and spices over bread.
Broil until brown; stir and brown the other side.

title: horseradish dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Serve over slices of beef or tomato and onions.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: whole sweet potato bake
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in buttered casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake in a 350° oven until heated through (25 to 30 minutes). Serves 4.

title: elephant stew
directions: After elephant is cleaned, add seasonings.
Cook in a very large pot outdoors.
Invite all the "Claiborne United Methodist Congregation."
Cook elephant for 4 to 5 days or until tender. If everybody shows up, add cut up rabbit, but only as a last resort, because most people don't like "hare" in their stew.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet; remove from the skillet.
Add 1 can of chicken broth and 1 can of water to the skillet, 1 cup of uncooked rice, dash of Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Stir well.

title: cornbread dressing and giblet gravy
directions: Combine bread, celery, onions and seasonings.
Mix well. Combine eggs and milk; pour over bread mixture.
Combine butter and broth; pour over mixture.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas onion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all together with 1/2 the cheese.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.
Top with remaining cheese and poppy seed.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: 'ono 'ono spareribs
directions: Have butcher crack bones to make 3 to 4-inch lengths.
Place ribs in large saucepan.
Add water to cover and the salt.
Bring to boiling; lower heat.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until ribs are almost tender.
Drain ribs well.
Cut into 1-rib sections.
Place in shallow glass dish.
Pour Tangy Barbecue Glaze over.
Let ribs marinate for several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain ribs, reserving glaze.
Place ribs on grill.
Grill 20 to 30 minutes, turning often and brushing generously with glaze until ribs are browned and evenly glazed.
Arrange ribs on tray or platter lined with lemon leaves, if you wish.
Makes about 36 appetizers.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, spices and 2 cups of cheese.
Mix well.
Place in deep dish casserole bowl.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: dream land potatoes
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs; mix until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Cream all ingredients together, except vanilla wafers, of course.
Use muffin pans and put muffin paper in each one.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each paper; fill cup 1/2 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until firm.
They will puff up.
Let stand a few minutes to cool and then they will fall.
Then top with a spoonful of cherries.
Makes about 2 dozen and they won't last long!

title: apple-topped pancakes
directions: Combine milk and butter in saucepan; cook over medium heat until butter melts. Remove from heat; cool to 105° to 115°. Combine yeast and warm water in a 1-cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes. Combine yeast mixture, milk mixture and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Cover and chill 8 hours. Stir.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box.
Use paper liners in muffin tins and fill half full.
Mix cream cheese with sugar, egg and salt.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop a teaspoon of this mixture into each batter-filled paper liner.
Bake according to package directions.
Freezes well.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: The day before serving mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Heat with 2 cups milk.
Boil until thickened.
Add egg yolks, water, butter and vanilla.
Mix. Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate whole wheat brownies
directions: Melt chocolate
and
allow
to cool.
Mix flour, baking powder and
salt;
set
aside.
Cream
butter
and sugar until fluffy. Beat
in
chocolate, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture and 1/2
cup nuts.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with
remaining
nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until brownies pull away from sides of pan and pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Peel, devein and almost split shrimp. Place, split side up, on a greased cookie sheet.
Melt butter. Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Sprinkle into shrimp.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes and serve.

title: tangy cheese spread
directions: Mix and beat; add enough Mullin's so the mixture is the color of pimento cheese.
Especially good with Triscuits.
You may want to double the recipe for a large party.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine in microwave proof bowl.
Cook on High 3 1/2 minutes; stir.
Cook again 3 1/2 minutes, then stir in 1 tablespoon oleo and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Stir in fast until foamy.
Pour onto buttered foil.

title: tasty mushrooms
directions: In
a
frypan
saute onion and margarine; add flour and stir until
slightly thickened.	Add mushrooms and cook until tender; add
paprika,
salt
and
pepper and thyme.
Add sour cream and stir
until
sour cream is heated.	Serve as a side dish.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly; empty into large bowl.
Add onion. Dissolve sugar in vinegar; add salt, pepper and oil to bean mixture.
Stir gently to blend.
Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce or by itself.

title: communion bread
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt. Add water to form dough. Roll out very thin (like pie crust). Cut into circles. Score into small squares and prick each square with toothpick. Bake at 225° to 250° about 30 minutes.

title: no bake date crisp cookies
directions: Place butter, sugar and dates in a pan. Boil 5 minutes on low heat. Remove and add the eggs, milk and salt. Boil 2 minutes more. Remove and add the Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts. Cool. Make in balls and roll in coconut.

title: broccoli & cheese casserole
directions: Heat oil in large sauce pan. Add onion. Cook stirring often, until softened and transparent. Stir in rice and broth. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 45 minutes. Meanwhile heat oven to 350 degrees. Coat an 8 x 8 glass baking dish with cooking spray. Mix broccoli, cheese and egg together with cooked rice. Spread mixture in baking dish. Bake for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs, soda and salt.
Mix flour and brans together in one bowl, mix buttermilk and water together in another container.
Alternately add dry ingredients and wet ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Mix well.
Grease muffin tins or use cupcake papers. Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: trout almondine
directions: Cut fillets into 6 portions.
Combine flour, salt and paprika. Roll portions into flour mixture.
Place in single layers, skin side down, in a well-greased baking dish.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over fillets.
Broil 4 inches from heat for about 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes evenly.
Saute almonds in remaining butter until brown.
Add lemon juice after removing from heat.
Add pepper sauce and parsley.
Pour over fillets and serve at once.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir corn syrup and sugar for 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and mix well.
Fold in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let stand 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake white cake mix according to directions on box.
Punch cake full of holes while still hot.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over hot cake.
Then pour cream of coconut over Eagle Brand.
Cover and let cool completely.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: leftover turkey or chicken
directions: Make a sauce with soup and milk; melt some Velveeta cheese in the soup mixture.
Add turkey or chicken, broccoli and potatoes. Then pour the mixture into a baking dish.
You can put bread crumbs or croutons on top if desired.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chili beans and rice
directions: Precook rice.
Microwave onion and bell pepper 2 to 3 minutes. Combine all ingredients except cheese in saucepan or skillet. Let simmer 10 or 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: ribbon nut bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, granulated sugar and egg; mix well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined oil, milk, eggs and peel, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Spread 1 cup batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with cream cheese mixture. Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: coconut candy bonbons
directions: Beat the margarine and confectioners sugar; add milk and vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Make into small balls.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: bob's venison fajitas
directions: Cut meat in thin strips.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Let stand 1/2 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Then put in marinade, Worcestershire sauce, red wine vinegar and Tony's seasoning.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cook meat on hot grill or in hot black iron skillet on stove.
Keep hot on side.
Saute onions and put on side.
Heat tortillas one at a time on griddle or in black iron skillet.
Place tortilla on a plate.
Make a line of venison.
Spoon on a line of sauteed onions.
Sprinkle on cheese, green onions, lettuce and picante.
Roll tortilla and enjoy! Great for breakfast.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute onion and pepper in small amount of butter.
In small bowl, mix sauteed onion and pepper with stuffing, 2/3 cup water, butter, salt, pepper and thyme until well blended.
For moist stuffing, add a little more water.
Insert stuffing in chops and place them in lightly buttered baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes more, uncovered, at 325°.

title: saucy sausage squares
directions: Line bottom of two 9 x 13-inch pans with dough from 2 packages of rolls.
Saute sausage in skillet.
Drain well.
Mix eggs with sausage and spread over dough in pans.
Mix cheese with spices.
Sprinkle over sausage.
Cover with dough from 2 remaining packages of rolls.
Brush egg over top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into little squares.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
May be frozen and reheated if desired.
Yield:
48 or more.

title: jello cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cracker crumbs and sugar.
Line 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Mix jello, sugar, water and pineapple juice and place in refrigerator until set.
Whip milk until peaks form.
Add pineapple and combine remaining ingredients and pour into crust.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour catsup on top before loaf is done.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs, one at a time, together.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Blend in syrup and mix together well.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool ten minutes before icing.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and egg in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Sift in flour and baking powder; blend well. Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: special cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda, oatmeal, coconut, nutmeats, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 or 10 minutes.

title: copper penny salad(marinated carrots)
directions: Slice carrots and cook until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper; mix with cooled carrots.
Heat other ingredients, stir and pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours.
This will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Serve cold.

title: po-boy, new orleans style
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add first 7 ingredients.
Pulse 5 times or until vegetables are finely chopped.
Place olive mixture in a bowl; cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Cut French bread in half horizontally using a serrated or electric knife.
Set top of each loaf aside.
Hollow out bottom half of each loaf, leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Spoon olive mixture evenly into each shell.
Layer sliced meats and cheeses evenly over olive mixture in each shell.
Replace top of each loaf.
To serve, cut each loaf crosswise into fourths.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: krusczyki(polish bow ties)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture adding milk; knead gently until smooth.
Roll out 1/3 of dough at a time on lightly floured surface; cut into strips 1/4-inch wide. Then cut diagonally about 3-inches apart.
Cut lengthwise, slit in center and pull one end through to make twisted shape.
Fry in oil a few at a time, until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Mash until creamy.
Add sugar, eggs, butter, milk, cinnamon, raisins and nuts (if desired). Pour into a baking dish and place marshmallows on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Let mixture be a little thin, perhaps add a little more milk.

title: baked brie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut crust from Brie; discard.
Spread Brie with 1/2 the butter and 1/2 the garlic.
Spread remaining butter and garlic in a baking dish.
Add parsley and almonds.
Bake to light brown, 20 minutes.
Add Brie to cover the butter mixture. Return to oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with chunks of sourdough French bread.

title: chicken cheese dip
directions: Reserve 1 teaspoon taco seasoning mix; set aside.
Combine remaining taco seasoning mix, chicken, beer and chilies in large skillet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until mix is thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in picante sauce.
Mash beans and garlic until smooth.
Spread bean mixture in a 10-inch dish.
Spoon chicken mixture evenly over bean mixture; top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Combine sour cream and reserved 1 teaspoon taco seasoning mix; spread over melted cheese.
Top with tomato, green onions and olives.
Serve with no-oil baked tortilla chips.

title: easy bake rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: whiskey sours(serves 12)
directions: Combine ingredients; stir well and garnish with cherries and lemon slices.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in a large bowl with electric mixer. Heat V-8 or tomato juice.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to hot tomato juice and stir thoroughly.
Add tomato-gelatin mix to salmon mix and blend.
Chill.

title: sausage savory
directions: Cut sausage in medium size slices.
Fry and drain grease off. Cut vegetables; place remaining ingredients in pot including sausage.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve over bed of rice.
Sausage can also be broken up after frying or can remain whole.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: If you are using beef roast, cook until tender with chopped onion.
If you are using ground beef, brown in skillet with chopped onion.
After cooking beef, drain.
Keep 1 cup of broth. Mix all ingredients and broth.
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot.
If you would like cheese grated on top, sprinkle with 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese before putting in oven. Serves 8.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Delicious on:
apples, pineapple, grapes and strawberries.

title: carrots with glaze
directions: Slice carrots round; boil until soft.
In a small saucepan, cook remaining ingredients until bubbly.
Pour over carrots.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine soups, broth, chilies and tomatoes.
Blend until smooth.
Place a layer of chicken in a casserole dish.
Add layer of tortillas, onion, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding a la supreme
directions: Mix in another bowl.
Blend the 2 mixtures together.
Then layer bananas, vanilla wafers and mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: oven brisket
directions: Rinse the blood off brisket and dry it with paper towels.
Trim off some of the fat.
Line a large, deep pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil that has been doubled.
Mix liquid smoke and Kitchen Bouquet and pour this on foil.
Place brisket on foil fat side up. Mix seasonings.
After mixing seasonings, add liquid smoke and Kitchen Bouquet and mix with seasonings to make a thin paste. Smear this all over top of brisket.
Add beer to pan.
Cover the pan with heavy-duty foil and crimp over edges of pan to seal.
Let marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours, or until tender.

title: macaroni luncheon casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and salt and pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs of bread and dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: In medium frying pan, melt butter.
Stir in onion and brown. Add mushroom soup, cheese, salt and carrots.
Pour into 8-cup casserole dish.
Place onion rings on top.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: melting minutes
directions: Mix together; teaspoon small balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 minutes to a delicate brown.
(Dust with sugar, nuts or coconut, if desired.)

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt butter. Cut up onions and saute onions in butter until clear. Add Philadelphia cream cheese and both cans of shrimp (water and all). Let cook on low fire until cream cheese is melted. Add cayenne pepper and serve with favorite chips.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut into bite size pieces the onion into rings.
Cover with dressing and let sit overnight.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut in pieces.
Mix chicken, onion, cheese, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes.
Soften tortillas in chicken broth; line tortillas in baking dish.
Add chicken mixture.
Combine soups and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: taco soup (variation)
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and oats, blending thoroughly.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Fill greased and floured muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until done.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Serve on lettuce or in dessert bowl.

title: spaghetti frittata
directions: Blend all ingredients together, and brown on one side in a small frying pan in a bit of olive oil.
Top with more cheese, and place under broiler until crusty and lightly browned on top. Serves 2 to 3 as an antipasto.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together sugar, cocoa and butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallow over cake.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can add a drop or two of food coloring to make pastel mints.
Roll small amounts of mixture into balls and place on wax paper, then flatten with fork.
Allow to harden.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes between
pint
and
1 quart sauce. Store in refrigerator.

title: 24-hour slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, pepper and carrot; set aside.
Bring other ingredients to a boil; pour over slaw.
Put in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
This slaw keeps well for up to 2 weeks.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine 2 tablespoons oil, egg and buttermilk; stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each wiener into 5 pieces.
Dip each piece into batter, coating completely.
(Use wooden picks to aid in dipping.) Pour oil to depth of 3 to 4 inches in a Dutch oven; heat to 375°. Fry pieces until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with mustard/ketchup, if desired.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and cherry juice.
Combine pineapple, fruit cocktail and apples.
Add to whipped cream.
Garnish with cherries and coconut.

title: peanut chocolate oat candy
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan until butter melts.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and chopped nuts.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.

title: daddy's shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: roquefort dressing (or bleu cheese)
directions: Beat all ingredients, except for Bleu cheese.
Make sure they are mixed well.
Add Bleu cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Melt margarine in pan, then mix cake mix and one egg in margarine in pan (use fork).
Then take cream cheese, two eggs and sugar and beat and put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix margarine and cookies.
Press into a 9-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows in milk and let cook a few minutes.
Stir in creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Whip 1 cup of heavy cream, then fold into mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell and freeze.
When ready to serve, top with remaining 1/2 cup heavy cream (whipped) and crushed cookies.

title: ginger creams
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine sugar, hot water, molasses, shortening and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Stir in remaining cookie ingredients until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting, or eat plain.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks; add baking powder, flour, butter, salt, sugar and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add egg whites.
Make sure waffle iron is very hot.
Pour 1/2 cup waffle mixture at a time onto iron. (Do not grease iron.)
Makes 8 or 9 waffles.

title: mounds balls(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Mix Alba '77, pineapple juice, coconut, vanilla and coconut extract together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and freeze. Makes 1 serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, sage, onions and butter, using 1/2 can of cream of chicken soup.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften mayonnaise and cream cheese and mix well.
Add green pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in shrimp well with mixer.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Wash and peel peaches.
Put cloves, cinnamon and pickling spices in a loose, clean, white cloth; tie top.
Cook together spices, sugar, vinegar and water 10 minutes.
Add peaches; cook slowly until tender.
Let sit overnight.
In the morning, remove spice bag.
Drain peaches. Boil syrup rapidly until thickened. Put peaches in sterile jars and pour syrup over peaches.
Seal. Process 20 minutes in boiling bath.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Sift 1 1/3 cups flour, 1 tablespoon of sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg and milk.
Mix together and pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Build up sides. Cover with rhubarb.
Sprinkle jello over rhubarb.

title: camille's fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail, then add Cool Whip, sliced bananas and pecans.
Mix together and serve.

title: broiled pork chops and onions
directions: Set oven control to broil.
Place pork chops on rack in broiler pan.
Broil with tops 3 to 5 inches from heat until light brown, about 10 minutes; turn pork.
Cut 1/4-inch slice from both ends of each onion.
Cut onions crosswise into halves; place in broiler pan with pork.
Sprinkle salt and sage over onions.
Broil until onions are light brown, about 5 minutes; turn onions. Sprinkle with salt and sage; drizzle with margarine.
Broil until pork is done, about 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over pork.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done (drain all grease).
Spread bread with butter.
Cut into cubes.
Place cubes into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over bread. Chill 8 hours or more.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fried corn(for 2)
directions: Heat bacon grease or butter in skillet.
Add all ingredients and fry for 7 to 10 minutes.
Has 170 calories per serving.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar.
Add one egg at a time and a little flour until all is gone.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: frozen peppermint cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into a spring-form pan.

title: busy day stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet, stirring often to crumble beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in mustard and soups.
Cover and let simmer until hot and bubbly.
Serve over noodles, creamed potatoes or toast.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of dressing and margarine.
Melt margarine and add to remaining dressing.
Spread on top of mixture.
Add a little sharp Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: mock fried mushrooms
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Be sure to use enough crackers to make a slightly dry mixture.
Make small patties and fry in vegetable oil.
Drain well.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir well.
Bake in covered baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy date squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and baking powder, sifted.
Add flavoring, nuts and dates.
Spread into pan that has been oiled and floured.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 325° oven.
Cut in squares.

title: southwestern nachos
directions: Combine 1/4 cup salsa with sour cream.
Spread tortilla chips on baking sheet.
Layer salsa mixture, chicken and cheese on chips.
Broil 2 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Spoon remaining salsa over cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jungle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Mix together broccoli, cheese, mayonnaise, soup, onion and egg in a 2 quart baking dish. Spread Stove Top Stuffing on top and drizzle with the melted margarine.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with a bay leaf for 1 hour on low heat.
Cool. Remove from bone and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix butter, soup and sour cream over low heat.
Pour over chicken. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Split canned biscuits and top casserole.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Make crust.
Cut apples in slices; mix sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Toss apples in mixture until all covered.
Put apples in crust with remaining sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with water and lemon juice.
Dot with butter pats.
Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven or until apples are cooked.
Serve with cheese or cream.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Bring vinegar, sugar, celery seed, dry mustard, oil and salt to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, pepper, onions and carrots.
Let chill before serving.

title: grits with cream and cheese
directions: Place grits and cream in a heavy saucepan (stirring). Cook grits according to package directions, using cream instead of water.
Stir often and do not let burn.
If grits start to get lumpy, add a little water to keep them creamy.
When cooked, remove from heat and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter and then stir in cheese. Can be reheated in microwave.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Wash and trim fat off of country style ribs.
Place in an oblong cake pan.
Layer with sliced onions.
