title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and margarine; let stand 20 minutes. Mix sugars; add eggs.
Sift salt, flour, cinnamon and soda.
Add to sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add oats to mixture; mix well. Spread batter in a greased 11 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in greased pan.
Mix soup, butter, cheese, sour cream, salt and onion together.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle melted butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent cristo sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise on one large or 2 small ungreased cookie sheets.
Rectangles shouldn't touch. Firmly press perforations to seal.
In small bowl, combine butter & 2 tablespoons honey, mix well.
Brush over dough.

Bake 375° for 8-12 minutes or until lightly golden brown. Cool 15 minutes. Grease 15x10x1 baking pan. Carefully place 1 crust on pan. Top evenly with turkey, place second crust over turkey, top with cheese & ham. Place third crust over ham and spread evenly with preserves or mustard. Top with fourth crust, brush top with 2 tablespoons honey and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Cook and stir beef, onion and celery. Dissolve bouillon in water; stir this and all other ingredients into meat.
Cover; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Crumble bacon on top or combine and heat on low in crock-pot 4 to 5 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Slice cookie roll and press together on pizza pan. Bake and cool.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Sprinkle
dry jello over cottage cheese and blend well. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat eggs slightly and mix with oil, strawberries and pecans.
Add ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or 6 to 8 small loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pans 5 minutes before removing.
Cool on wire racks.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with graham crackers.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecan pieces over crackers.
Bring butter, margarine and sugar to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Cut between crackers while hot and take them right up.
Cool on foil.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water. Mix ingredients, and make into biscuits. Put on baking sheet and rise 30 minutes to 1 hour. Bake at 400°. Makes 29 biscuits. Can half
each of the ingredients to make fewer biscuits.

title: green chili cheese and rice
directions: Cut Jack cheese into 1/2-inch squares.
Combine with sour cream, chilies, rice and pepper in a small casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with shredded Cheddar and let sit a few minutes as cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: warm rice salad
directions: Heat 2 1/2 cups water with salt in saucepan to boiling.
Add rice and stir.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook, covered, until water is absorbed, 12 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: sin
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and oleo in bottom of dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients on High 4 minutes (cook 2 minutes, stir, cook 2 minutes). Add the soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup over the popped corn in a large grocery sack.
Close and shake. Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes; shake. Cook 1 1/2 minutes and shake.
Cook 45 seconds and shake.
Cook 30 seconds and shake. Pour onto cookie sheets to cool.
Not sticky and easy to clean up.

title: margaret's pecan pie and crust
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: baked apple turnovers
directions: Cut pastry into 8 (4 1/2-inch) circles.
Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons of cooked apples on one-half of each circle.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold dough over apple mixture, pressing edges to seal.
Crimp edges with a fork.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; put in 3 egg yolks and add milk gradually until mixed.
Cook slow, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool.
Add coconut (save a little for meringue).
Put in baked pie shell.
Make meringue by beating 3 egg whites, adding 6 tablespoons sugar.
Pour on top of pie and sprinkle coconut on top.
Brown at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Combine flour and sugar.
Add milk and butter to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased or buttered baking dish.
Arrange peach slices on top of batter.
Peaches will sink and batter will bake up around them.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and bottom dough is baked.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold.
Add crushed pineapple, cran-orange relish, celery and nuts. Top or mix in Cool Whip or omit entirely.
Refrigerate overnight. Serves quite a few people.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix margarine, sugar and egg.
Grate apples to equal 2 cups.
Add and mix just until blended.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer slowly for about 1 hour or until desired thickness.

title: microwave pecan candy
directions: Mix sugar and whipping cream in Pyrex or other microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High for 7 minutes.
Stir and cook 7 more minutes on High.
Add margarine, vanilla extract and pecans.
Stir well and cook an additional 2 minutes on High.
Stir for about 1/2 to one minute.
Scoop out on waxed paper (about 2 heaping tablespoonfuls for each piece).

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings.
Cut at joint.
Combine ingredients and marinate several hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy berry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Then fold in berries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Add boiling water and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: stuffed mushrooms 2
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients, stuff mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put in a large bowl the cake mix, eggs, cooking oil, dry vanilla pudding and water and mix.
Beat for 8 minutes.
Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Put half of this mixture on the cake mixture and add remaining cake mixture and remaining sugar mixture.
Take a spoon and mix to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. You may drizzle powdered sugar icing over cooled baked cake.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt to simmering over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Place popped corn in large bowl and pour hot mixture over top.
Toss with spoon to coat.
Place on large cookie sheet in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour to harden.
Be sure to grease cookie sheet well.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add sour cream and pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in pineapple, walnuts and celery. Pour into a 7-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and pineapple chunks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt into large mixing bowl.
Stir in butter, egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add sugar and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls, flattening on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make prints on top with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 675°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
With fork, mashed the cranberry sauce into the gelatin mixture.
Add pineapple and mix. Place in the refrigerator to gel.
Mix cream cheese and sugar. Blend, then place on top of the jello mixture.
Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: sugar-free apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Coat apples with NutraSweet and cinnamon.
Put apple mixture in pie crust and put pats of butter on top of apples.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in shortening. Add 4 tablespoons flour and slowly add 2 cups broth. add chicken, peas, potatoes and carrots (cooked). Put in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with a few cherries.

title: easy party sausages
directions: Combine in a crock-pot and heat until bubbling.
This can be used for frozen meat balls as well.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat for 10 minutes the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter, eggs and vanilla.
Be sure to beat for 10 minutes.
Put on top of crust.
Slice 5 or 6 bananas and put on top of mixture.
Put pineapple, drained, on top of bananas.
Put Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Grind nuts and put on top of Cool Whip.
Cut cherries and put on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Let set for 24 hours.
Enjoy!

title: carrot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in container of electric blender. Process on high speed until smooth.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Yield:
1 pie.

title: chocolate nut clusterssocorro, new mexico
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double broiler or small bowl set over hot water.
Stir in shortening and cinnamon until well blended and smooth.
Stir in nuts until coated.
Remove from heat.

title: five minute icing
directions: Stir together vanilla pudding and milk with fork until thick. Turn in powdered sugar, then fold in the Cool Whip and spread on well cooled cake.

title: french chicken
directions: Lay chicken in foil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Make loose tent with foil over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover for additional 15 minutes until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat well. Add eggs and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat 3 eggs lightly and mix in Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses, 2 tablespoons butter, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Also, add cooked and drained spinach.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate milk and flour until all are mixed.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° or until done.

title: lemon fingers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press evenly into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (moisten fingers to avoid sticking).
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° .
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over baked bottom layer.
Return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into fingers or squares when cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, margarine and peanut butter together.
Shape into balls, size of walnut.
Melt the wax in top of double boiler.
Add chocolate bits; blend.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Chill until firmly set.
Makes about 4 dozen.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be frozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Marinate overnight kidney beans and Cheddar cheese, then add Catalina dressing to beans mixture when ready to serve.
Serve with onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Cover with Frito-Lay corn chips.

title: yogurt
directions: Heat milk to almost boiling (180°) to kill undesirable bacteria.
Add gelatin, which has been soaked in 1/4 cup water. Add sugar and flavoring, if desired.
Cool to lukewarm; a little warmer is better.
Add a level tablespoon leftover yogurt for starter.
Bought yogurt may be used, but usually works slower. Set in warm place until thick.
Three to 4 hours makes the mildest yogurt.
Whip with beater and refrigerate.
Serve with fruit.

title: southern corn casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil, stirring occasionally.
Add onion and pepper, cook until tender.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.
(Or put in casserole and grate 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.)

title: apple "schnarks"
directions: Pour pie filling into oblong pan.
Sprinkle entire cake mix over.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven, or until golden brown.
Great with ice cream on top!

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with bacon.
Secure with toothpicks. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet.
Drain.
Broil 2 minutes.
Mix together sugar, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Put chestnuts in casserole and pour mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 10 more minutes.
Serve warm.

title: asparagus and tomato pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package, adding asparagus for the last 2 minutes; drain. Rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine the whole-kernel corn, cream style corn, sour cream, melted butter, beaten eggs and Jiffy mix.
Mix well and pour into 9x13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut up and boil potatoes.
Drain and mash them.
Add remaining ingredients and whip with electric beater until smooth.
Put into greased casserole dish and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add all else and mix.
Put cheese on top.
Bake in a buttered dish at 350° for one hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all.
Put in 9 x 9-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be mixed the day before and stored in refrigerator before baking.

title: oven "french fried" zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to very hot 475°.
Spray a nonstick cookie sheet liberally with cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper on a sheet of waxed paper.
Quarter zucchini lengthwise, then slice each spear in half to make shorter spears.
Put them in plastic bag; add oil and water.
Close bag and shake so spears are lightly coated with oil.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes, until well browned.

title: poires helene
directions: In the bottom of each cup or bowl, put 2 tablespoon chocolate syrup.
On top of syrup, place 1 or scoops of ice cream.
Place one pear half, cut side down, on top of each portion of ice cream. Combine jam and water in a separate bowl; spoon mixture over each pear.

title: potato pancakes supreme with onions
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add grated onion, salt and pepper, with beaten eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Have griddle hot. Spoon on greased griddle 2 tablespoons of batter for each pancake. Fry to a golden brown.
Try applesauce on top.

title: christmas tree appetizers
directions: You will need 1 purchased 10-inch styrofoam cone and toothpicks to assemble appetizers.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs under broiler and drain off the excess fat. Brown onion in fat.
Combine lemon juice, brown sugar, salt, pepper, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, water and celery. Add ingredients to sauteed onion.
Pour sauce over spareribs in large baking pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour or more, until well done.
Serves 4.

title: wild crab casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion, mushrooms, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper in butter until tender.
Slowly add flour, then cream.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Stir egg yolks into 1 cup of cream sauce.
Return to hot mixture; stir constantly until it boils. Add cheese, rice and crabmeat.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: sour cream pecan coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Mix until smooth; add vanilla.

title: carrot raisin slaw
directions: Combine all. Mix well. Cover and chill.

title: six minute frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add butter, milk and Karo and bring to full boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 6 minutes.
Cool mixture for 15 minutes.
Add flavoring and beat until creamy.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour onto a buttered platter.
Cut when cold.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Then dip in beaten egg white and cornflake crumbs.
Fry and serve with a cheese sauce.

title: pasta primavera with stir-fried chicken
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, cut asparagus into 2-inch pieces.
Thinly slice mushrooms and carrots.
Cut zucchini lengthwise in half, then crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut green onions into 3-inch pieces.
Remove bones from chicken breasts; cut meat into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon of salt until blended.
Gradually stir in milk; add bouillon and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Keep sauce warm.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Crush strawberries (about 1 cup); add 1/2 cup sugar and let stand 30 minutes.
Soften gelatin in water; dissolve over low heat; cool.
Add strawberries, lemon juice and dash of salt. Chill, stirring occasionally, until partially set.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in strawberry mixture, then whipped cream. Chill until mixture mounds. Pile into cooled shell. Chill firm, about 5 hours.
Trim with whipped cream.

title: bran date muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran.
Mix remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Batter can be mixed ahead.
Keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pink monkey salad
directions: Soften gelatine
in cold water.
Add tomato soup.
Stir over low heat
until
gelatine
is
dissolved.
Stir
in cream cheese; cool
slightly.
Add mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.	Pour into
quart
ring mold.
Chill until firm.	Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with stuffed olives (sliced).
Lay strips of bell pepper to form wreaths on salad.

title: hot cheese tuna sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Mound onto buttered muffins and cover with cheese.
Run under broiler until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 3.

title: quick beef and cheese empanadillas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain well. Stir in chili sauce; set aside.
Unroll dough into four long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides, firmly pressing perforations and edges to seal.
Pat to form 15 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread meat mixture lengthwise, in a 4-inch strip down center of dough, to within 1 inch of ends.
Top with cheese slices.
Fold ends in.
Bring long sides over filling, overlapping edges.
Pinch edges to seal.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (except nuts) for about 2 minutes combining well.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of greased tube pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 325° until done, 1 hour or less.
Remove from oven and pierce top with toothpick.
Pour glaze over top of cake. Cool before removing from pan.

title: challot
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, eggs and 6 cups of flour; beat well.
Add more flour gradually, until stiff.
Place on floured board and knead, adding flour, if necessary.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Place dough in a large bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place 1 1/2 hours, until triple in bulk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini in oil and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Add egg, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour into 1 greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sassafras tea (papa's recipe)
directions: Wash sassafras roots well and cut into 2 or 3-inch pieces.
Add roots to 1/2 gallon water.
Bring to a boil.
Add soda and boil for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
After mixture cools, strain tea from roots.
Add sugar and 1/2 gallon water (or as needed).
Serve hot.
"It's good for what ails you."

title: potato crispies
directions: Combine the potatoes, onion, flour, sour cream, eggs and salt. Heat the lard in a large frying pan.
Drop the potato mixture (2 heaping teaspoons per cake) into the hot lard.
With a spatula, flatten slightly to make 3-inch circles.
Fry 4 to 5 minutes, until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 16 cakes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers, cocoa, powdered sugar and chopped nuts.
Stir this well.
Mix bourbon and syrup together well.
Pour the liquid bourbon and syrup into the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
If too dry, add more bourbon.
If too wet, add more crumbs or sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion.
Drain.
Mix cheese, mayo, soup and eggs (beaten).
Add to broccoli.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbs or chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fatigman
directions: Roll out like pie crust, only thinner.
Cut into triangles with crinkle cutter.
Put slit in center.
Put tail into slit. Drop into hot deep fat until golden brown.
Remove; sprinkle powdered sugar on while warm.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon with cup of hot water.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend butter, flour, salt and stir in milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add cheese.
Heat until cheese melts, take from stove.

title: ham and vegetable dish
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Don't overcook.
Lightly grease 1 1/2 quart casserole and line bottom with ham, drained vegetables and cheese.
If desired, top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and vanilla; bring to boil in heavy saucepan. At soft ball stage remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Cool to lukewarm; beat until desired consistency; pour in greased dish. Cut when cool.

title: english rice pudding
directions: Cover rice with boiling water and let stand overnight.
Step 1: Heat oven to 325°.

Drain rice, cover with fresh boiling water. Bake until water is almost absorbed, 10 to 15 minutes.* Step 2: Turn oven down to 300°; add sugar, nutmeg and some of the milk. Stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Step 3:
Add remaining milk and raisins (if used); return to oven for approximately 2 hours.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces (about 1 inch size). Using a trifle bowl or glass bowl, layer 1/2 of torn angel food cake into bowl.
Combine pudding (mixed as directed on box) and Cool Whip.
Layer 1/2 pudding over cake.
Layer third 1 1/2 cups of sliced fruit of your choice.
Continue layering cake, pudding and fruit.
Save enough pudding to cover top.
Decorate top with a few pieces of fruit.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: sharon's french silk pie
directions: Melt and let cool semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Beat until light and fluffy (5 to 10 minutes) the butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat 3 minutes after each. Carefully and quickly blend in melted chocolate chips.
Pour into baked, cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When set, top with whipped cream, chocolate Hershey bar curls and almonds.
Keep pie in refrigerator.
Let sit at room temperature 20 minutes before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Doritos in large bowl.

title: slaw
directions: Chop up carrot and green pepper.
Mix with cabbage.
Pour liquid over after cooled.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil potatoes and 1 teaspoon sugar together until potatoes are tender; drain.
Add pickle relish and onion; set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over potato mixture to coat.
Refrigerate several hours to allow flavors to blend.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Alternate layers of shrimp and onion in large shallow bowl or casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and refrigerate.
Marinate at least 24 hours, turning shrimp three or four times.
Serve with Tangy Sauce.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: In large casserole, sprayed with Pam, layer eggplant slices and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Make several layers of eggplant slices and cheeses.
Saute turkey, onion, garlic, mushrooms.
Add tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour turkey mixture over eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium bowl, combine milk powder and sugar substitute and set aside.
In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water and let stand to soften, about 1 minute; add peanut butter and cook, stirring constantly, until peanut butter is melted and gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into milk mixture and add whipped topping and sunflower seeds; using a wooden spoon, mix until thoroughly combined.
Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam and pour peanut butter mixture into the pan, using a spatula to spread evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sandy's rolls
directions: Add sugar and salt to the melted shortening; cool.
Add egg. Add yeast.
Add flour.
Cover and refrigerate.
After chilled, roll out 1/4 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Spread with butter.
Top with another one.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.

title: grandpa's wilted cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage finely.
Sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Add onion.
Let this mixture stand in refrigerator for 1 hour, until seasoned.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Add diced bacon to seasoned cabbage.
Mix well.
Add vinegar to bacon grease in pan, heat to boiling.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix and serve.
This dish should be served warm, not hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, flavoring and 2/3 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining 1/3 cup of milk and 2 eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake in layer pans 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice as desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; reserve 2/3 cup chicken broth.
In medium pan, melt butter.
Slowly pour in 1 cup Bisquick; mix until smooth. Pour milk, a little at a time, stirring.
Mixture will thicken. Add vegetables, salt and pepper.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Place in ice cream freezer.
Fill freezer with milk until 2/3 full.

title: big boy strawberry pie (glazed)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and clear, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add strawberry Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate to cool, about 10 minutes.
Slice fresh strawberries in bottom of 8 or 9-inch baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mix over berries and chill. Top with Cool Whip.

title: hommus dip
directions: In 2-quart pot, empty cans of peas and juice from one can.
Add olive oil, red pepper, Feta cheese, oregano and salt.
Heat for 5 minutes.

title: seafood cocktail dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: super nacho dip
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients in the order given. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in 450° oven for 45 minutes.

title: patio punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ice and ginger ale and chill.
When ready to serve, pour in ginger ale and serve over ice.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: golden cream cheese soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley and bouillon cube. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Gradually add milk to flour; mixing well.
Add milk mixture to vegetables. Cook until thickened. Add Velveeta; stir until melted.

title: okie cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the first four ingredients.
In a pot, bring the water, cocoa and butter
to a boil.
Pour over the dry ingredients and add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix and bake in a jelly roll pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: squash cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trippledecr sandwech
directions: U take 1 slis of bred and put sum manas on it. Then put sum ham r blany on it weth a slis of cheaz.
On your secun slis of bred put some mustrd on it weth sum ham r blany and a slis of cheaz.
On your 3 slis put sum manas on it and put sum ham r blony and sum cheaz.
Put it all toogethr and u have a treppledecr.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger with the onion, then drain grease.
Mix olives, enchilada sauce and
tomato sauce with hamburger; cook 10 minutes.
In a 9 x	13-inch
dish, use 6 flour taco shells. Add 1/2 filling, then add 6 more shells on top of that and the remaining
filling.
Then on
top,
add
package
shredded Longhorn cheese and 1 package Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spam casserole
directions: Follow directions on macaroni dinner box.
Dice Spam and add to noodles when done.
Add cream of mushroom soup as well.
Bake in casserole dish for 25 minutes and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and flour. Add Karo, pecans, butter and vanilla. Stir well and pour into pie shells.
Bake until firm, usually 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry cheese brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs.
Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 20 minutes.

title: fat-free pear upside-down cake
directions: Drain pears; save juice.
Coat a 9-inch ovenproof skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons of pear juice in bottom of skillet and distribute evenly.
Sprinkle the brown sugar evenly over pear juice.
Arrange 10 pear halves over the brown sugar with the cut side down and the widest part of pears toward outer edge.
Fill in center with pecan halves, if desired.

title: mustard sauce for ham loaf
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Serve on ham loaf.
It is best if it is hot when you serve it.

title: josephine's coleslaw
directions: Cut cabbage into 4 quarters and shred.
Take all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.
A great alternative!

title: traditional marble pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Mix in flour, 1/3 at a time.
Mix cocoa, baking soda and boiling water until smooth in a medium bowl; add 1 1/2 cups of cake batter, stirring well.

title: spanish paella(pie-a-ya)
directions: Need a large pot (shallow).

title: chicken divine
directions: Put chicken in pan, cover with cheese.
Dilute soup with wine. Mix melted butter with stuffing mix.
Put over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma's crazy crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Melt butter in 10-inch pie plate.
Pour batter on top of melted butter.
Add fruit or pie filling in middle of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook ground beef, onions and bell pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain.
Add noodles and remainder of ingredients except add only half of the cheese.
Mix well.
Pour in an ungreased 2-quart casserole and top with remainder of cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese begins to brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes more.
Place chicken pieces on plate and serve the gravy over rice.
(Top chicken with the fruit.)

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in parsley or chopped nuts.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownie mix as directed on package.
Poke holes in brownies and pour Kahlua over brownies; let cool and crumble.
In a large bowl, put in 1/2 of crumbled brownies, 1/2 of Heath bars, 1 package of mousse and cover with Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip, then drizzle chocolate syrup over the top.

title: cabbage creole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain well and place in casserole.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add tomatoes with juice, sugar, salt and pepper and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sausage and pour mixture over cabbage. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: wild rice - ground beef(serves 12)
directions: Cook rice according to direction on box.
Set aside.
Grease well 1 very large or 2 medium casseroles.
In Dutch oven brown meat, breaking it up as it cooks and browns.
Next add onion and bay leaves.
Add all the rest of the ingredients and the rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into the baking dish or dishes.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
(This step is important to develop the flavors.)
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 2 hours.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients except the pecans and cook to a soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the pecans; stir until they are evenly coated.
Pour out onto waxed paper and cool.
When cool, separate into pieces.

title: sharon's veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: special english pea salad
directions: Mix above ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Crumble cooked bacon on top.

title: "batter" for shrimp, chicken or steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, beaten egg with oil and water, milk or beer. Beat with mixer until smooth.
This should be like a heavy cream. Do not add any more liquids.
Let stand for 1 hour at room temperature.
Dip meat in batter until completely covered.
Allow excess to drip off.
Deep fry in corn oil at 375° until golden brown.
Drain.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. In a large bowl, blend all bar ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and cool.

title: pralines
directions: Put all ingredients in a medium saucepan and cook, stirring continuously, until a drop of mixture hardens in cool water. Spread on buttered platter.
When hard, cut and serve.

title: sliced cucumbers
directions: Slice at least 4 cucumbers and mix well with above mixture. Put lid on airtight container (glass or plastic).
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 3 months.
Do not add water.

title: sweet and sour chicken stir fry(heritage recipe)
directions: Stir together, until well blended, apricot spread, vinegar, garlic powder, ginger, soy sauce and crushed red pepper.
Set aside.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peak forms. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Blend in egg yolks and lemon juice. Gently fold in La Creme. Spoon into baked pie crust. Freeze 2 to 3 hours, until firm. Allow defrosting 15 minutes before slicing. Re-freeze unused portion.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Peel and dice baked sweet potato.
Cut potato and margarine into flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add butter flavoring to milk and add to mixture.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Turn onto floured board and knead gently.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for about 12 minutes (yields about 1 dozen).
A Blair kitchen-tested recipe.
Delicious, delightfully different.

title: crustless zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients until zucchini is evenly coated.
Pour into buttered 10 x 6-inch or 13 x 4-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 portions.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Add pretzels; mix well. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream sit on counter until softened.
Take package of cookies and reduce to crumbs (pea size).
Mix the two together. Pour into a spring-form pan.
Cover with foil.
Store in freezer for 24 hours.
Take out of freezer; remove sides of pan and frost with Cool Whip.
Add sprinkles, jimmies or nuts.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Place the pecans in the bottom of an unbaked crust.
Pour the filling over the pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: turkey boat
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir to make smooth paste. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
When thickened, add cheese and stir until melted.
Add turkey, onion and salt.
Hollow out buns, leaving a 1-inch wall of bread on bottom and sides.
Place on baking sheet and divide mixture between boats.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° in oven until browned.
Serves 6.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and combine beans.
Dice onion and add remaining ingredients to beans.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine soup bone, water and salt in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour.
Trim tops from green onions.
Chop bulbs and tops separately and set aside. Saute onion bulbs and okra in hot bacon drippings 10 minutes.
Add tomato and saute about 5 minutes.
Add 6 cups soup stock, green onion tops and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Yield: about 2 quarts.
